\mt2 ¶ THE BOOKE OF
\mt1 Ioshua.
\ie
\cl CHAP.
\c 1
\v 0 1 The \nd LORD\nd* appointeth Ioshua to succeede Moses. 3 The borders of the promised land. 5. 9 God promiseth to assist Ioshua. 8 He giueth him instructions. 10 He prepareth the people to passe ouer Iordan. 12 Ioshua putteth the two tribes and halfe in minde of their promise to Moses. 16 They promise him fealty.
\v 1 ¶ Nowe after the death of Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd*, it came to passe, that the \nd LORD\nd* spake vnto Ioshua the sonne of Nun, Moses \f + \fr 1:1 \ft Deut. 1. 38.\f*minister, saying,
\v 2 Moses my seruant is dead: now therefore arise, goe ouer this Iordan, thou, and all this people, vnto the land which I doe giue to them, \add euen\add* to the children of Israel.
\v 3 \f + \fr 1:3 \ft Deut.11. 24. chap. 14.9.\f*Euery place that the sole of your foote shall tread vpon, that haue I giuen vnto you, as I said vnto Moses.
\v 4 From the wildernesse and this Lebanon, euen vnto the great Riuer, the riuer Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites, and vnto the great sea, toward the going downe of the Sunne, shalbe your coast.
\v 5 There shall not any man be able to stand before thee all the dayes of thy life: as I was with Moses, \add so\add* I will be with thee: \f + \fr 1:5 \ft Heb. 13. 6.\f*I will not faile thee, nor forsake thee.
\v 6 \f + \fr 1:6 \ft Deut. 31. 23.\f*Bee strong, and of a good courage: for \f + \fr 1:6 \ft Or, thou shalt cause this people inherite the land, &c.\f*vnto this people shalt thou diuide for an inheritance the land which I sware vnto their fathers to giue them.
\v 7 Onely bee thou strong, and very courageous, that thou mayest obserue to doe according to all the Law, which Moses my seruant commaunded thee: \f + \fr 1:7 \ft Deu. 5.32 and 28. 14.\f*turne not from it \add to\add* the right hand, or \add to\add* the left, that thou mayest \f + \fr 1:7 \ft Or, doe wisely.\f*prosper whither soeuer thou goest.
\v 8 This booke of the Law shal not depart out of thy mouth, but thou shalt meditate therein day and night, that thou mayest obserue to doe according to all that is written therein: for then thou shalt make thy way prosperous, and then thou shalt \f + \fr 1:8 \ft Or, doe wisely.\f*haue good successe.
\v 9 Haue not I commanded thee? be strong, and of a good courage, bee not afraid, neither be thou dismayed: for the \nd LORD\nd* thy God \add is\add* with thee, whither soeuer thou goest.
\v 10 ¶ Then Ioshua commanded the Officers of the people, saying,
\v 11 Passe through the hoste, and command the people, saying, Prepare you victuals: for within three dayes ye shal passe ouer this Iordan, to goe in to possesse the land which the \nd LORD\nd* your God giueth you, to possesse it.
\v 12 ¶ And to the Reubenites, and to the Gadites, and to halfe the tribe of Manasseh, spake Ioshua, saying,
\v 13 \f + \fr 1:13 \ft Num.32 20.\f*Remember the word which Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* commanded you, saying, The \nd LORD\nd* your God hath giuen you rest, and hath giuen you this land:
\v 14 Your wiues, your litle ones, and your cattell shall remaine in the lande which Moses gaue you on this side Iordan; but ye shall passe before your brethren \f + \fr 1:14 \ft Heb. marshalled by fiue.\f*armed, all the mightie men of valour, and helpe them:
\v 15 Untill the \nd LORD\nd* haue giuen your brethren rest, as \add he hath giuen\add* you, and they also haue possessed the lande which the \nd LORD\nd* your God giueth them: then yee shall returne vnto the land of your possession, and enioy it, which Moses the \nd LORD\nd*s seruant gaue you on this side Iordan toward the Sunne rising.
\v 16 ¶ And they answered Ioshua, saying, All that thou commandest vs, we will doe, and whither soeuer thou sendest vs, we will goe.
\v 17 According as we hearkened vnto Moses in all things, so will we hearken vnto thee: onely the \nd LORD\nd* thy God be with thee, as he was with Moses.
\v 18 Whosoeuer \add he be\add* that doth rebell against thy commandement, and will not hearken vnto thy words, in all that thou commandest him, he shall bee put to death: onely be strong, and of a good courage.
\c 2
\v 0 1 Rahab receiueth and concealeth the two spies sent from Shittim. 8 The couenant betweene her and them. 23 Their returne and relation.
\v 1 ¶ And Ioshua the sonne of Nun sent out of Shittim two men, to spie secretly, saying, Go, view the land, euen Iericho: and they went, and \f + \fr 2:1 \ft Heb.11. 31 iam.2. 25.\f*came into an harlots house, named Rahab, and \f + \fr 2:1 \ft Heb. lay.\f*lodged there.
\v 2 And it was told the king of Iericho, saying, Behold, there came men in hither to night, of the children of Israel, to search out the countrey.
\v 3 And the king of Iericho sent vnto Rahab, saying, Bring forth the men that are come to thee, which are entred into thine house: for they bee come to search out all the countrey.
\v 4 And the woman tooke the two men, and hid them, & said thus: There came men vnto mee, but I wist not whence they \em were\em*:
\v 5 And it came to passe \em about the time\em* of shutting of the gate, when it was darke, that the men went out: whither the men went, I wote not: pursue after them quickely, for ye shall ouertake them.
\v 6 But shee had brought them vp to the roofe of the house, and hid them with the stalkes of flaxe, which she had laid in order vpon the roofe.
\v 7 And the men pursued after them the way to Iordan, vnto the foords: and assoone as they which pursued after them were gone out, they shut the gate.
\v 8 ¶ And before they were laide downe, shee came vp vnto them vpon the roofe.
\v 9 And she said vnto the men, I know that the \nd LORD\nd* hath giuen you the land, and that your terrour is fallen vpon vs, and that all the inhabitants of the land \f + \fr 2:9 \ft Heb. melt.\f*faint because of you:
\v 10 For wee haue heard how the \nd LORD\nd* \f + \fr 2:10 \ft Exod.14 21. chap. 4. 23.\f*dried vp the water of the red Sea for you; when you came out of Egypt, and what you did vnto the two kings of the Amorites that \em were\em* on the other side Iordan, \f + \fr 2:10 \ft Num.21 24.\f*Sihon and Og; whom ye vtterly destroyed.
\v 11 And assoone as we had heard \em these things\em*, our hearts did melt, neither did there \f + \fr 2:11 \ft Heb. rose vp.\f*remaine any more courage in any man, because of you: for the \nd LORD\nd* your God, he \em is\em* God in heauen aboue, and in earth beneath.
\v 12 Now therfore, I pray you, sweare vnto me by the \nd LORD\nd*, since I haue shewed you kindnesse, that ye will also shew kindnesse vnto my fathers house, and giue me a true token:
\v 13 And \em that\em* ye will saue aliue my father, and my mother, and my brethren, and my sisters, and all that they haue, and deliuer our liues from death.
\v 14 And the men answered her, Our life \f + \fr 2:14 \ft Hebr. in stead of you to die.\f*for yours, if yee vtter not this our businesse. And it shall bee when the \nd LORD\nd* hath giuen vs the land, that wee will deale kindely and truely with thee.
\v 15 Then shee let them downe by a coard thorow the window: for her house \em was\em* vpon the towne wall, and she dwelt vpon the wall.
\v 16 And she said vnto them, Get you to the mountaine, lest the pursuers meete you; and hide your selues there three dayes, vntill the pursuers bee returned, and afterward may ye goe your way.
\v 17 And the men said vnto her, Wee will bee blamelesse of this thine oath which thou hast made vs sweare:
\v 18 Behold, \em when\em* we come into the land, thou shalt binde this line of scarlet threed in the window which thou didst let vs downe by: and thou shalt \f + \fr 2:18 \ft Hebr. gather.\f*bring thy father and thy mother, and thy brethren, and all thy fathers houshold home vnto thee.
\v 19 And it shall bee, \em that\em* whosoeuer shall goe out of the doores of thy house into the street, his blood \em shalbe\em* vpon his head, and wee will bee guiltlesse: and whosoeuer shall bee with thee in the house, his blood \em shalbe\em* on our head, if \em any\em* hand be vpon him.
\v 20 And if thou vtter this our businesse, then we wilbe quit of thine oath which thou hast made vs to sweare.
\v 21 And shee saide, According vnto your words, so \em be\em* it. And she sent them away, & they departed: and she bound the scarlet line in the window.
\v 22 And they went, and came vnto the mountaine, and abode there three dayes, vntill the pursuers were returned. And the pursuers sought \em them\em* thorowout all the way, but found \em them\em* not.
\v 23 ¶ So the two men returned, and descended from the mountaine, and passed ouer, and came to Ioshua the sonne of Nun, and told him all \em things\em* that befell them.
\v 24 And they saide vnto Ioshua, Truely the \nd LORD\nd* hath deliuered into our hands all the land; for euen all the inhabitants of the countrey doe \f + \fr 2:24 \ft Hebr. melt.\f*faint because of vs.
\c 3
\v 0 1 Ioshua commeth to Iordan. 2 The Officers instruct the people for the passage. 7 The\nd LORD\nd* incourageth Ioshua. 9 Ioshua incourageth the people. 14 The waters of Iordan are diuided.
\v 1 ¶ And Ioshua rose early in the morning, and they remooued from Shittim, and came to Iordan, hee and all the children of Israel, and lodged there before they passed ouer.
\v 2 And it came to passe after three dayes, that the Officers went thorow the hoste;
\v 3 And they commanded the people, saying, When ye see the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd* your God, and the Priests the Leuites bearing it, then yee shall remooue from your place, and goe after it.
\v 4 \f + \fr 3:4 \ft Hebr. since yesterday & the third day.\f*Yet there shalbe a space betweene you and it, about two thousand cubites by measure: come not neere vnto it, that ye may know the way by which ye must goe: for yee haue not passed \add this\add* way heretofore.
\v 5 \f + \fr 3:5 \ft Leuit. 20.7. num.11. 18. chap. 7. 13. 1.sam. 16.5.\f*And Ioshua said vnto the people, Sanctifie your selues: for to morrow the \nd LORD\nd* wil do wōders among you.
\v 6 And Ioshua spake vnto the Priests, saying, Take vp the Arke of the Couenant, and passe ouer before the people. And they tooke vp the Arke of the Couenant, and went before the people.
\v 7 ¶ \f + \fr 3:7 \ft Chap.1. 5.\f*And the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto Ioshua, This day wil I begin to magnifie thee in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that as I was with Moses, \add so\add* I will be with thee.
\v 8 And thou shalt commaund the Priests that beare the Arke of the Couenant, saying; When ye are come to the brinke of the water of Iordan, yee shall stand still in Iordan.
\v 9 ¶ And Ioshua said vnto the children of Israel, Come hither, and heare the words of the \nd LORD\nd* your God.
\v 10 And Ioshua said, Hereby ye shall know that the liuing God \add is\add* among you, and \add that\add* he will without faile driue out from before you the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Hiuites, and the Perizzites, and Girgashites, and the Amorites, and the Iebusites.
\v 11 Behold, the Arke of the Couenant, euen the \nd LORD\nd* of all the earth, passeth ouer before you, into Iordan.
\v 12 Now therefore take yee twelue men out of the Tribes of Israel, out of euery Tribe a man.
\v 13 \f + \fr 3:13 \ft Psal. 114. 3.\f*And it shall come to passe, assoone as the soles of the feete of the Priestes that beare the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*, the \nd LORD\nd* of all the earth, shall rest in the waters of Iordan, \add that\add* the waters of Iordan shall be cut off, \add from\add* the waters that come downe from aboue: and they shall stand vpon an heape.
\v 14 ¶ \f + \fr 3:14 \ft Acts 7.45.\f*And it came to passe when the people remooued from their tents, to passe ouer Iordan, and the Priests bearing the Arke of the Couenant before the people;
\v 15 \f + \fr 3:15 \ft 1. Chron. 12.15. ecclus. 24.30.\f*And as they that bare the Arke were come vnto Iordan, and the feet of the Priestes that bare the Arke, were dipped in the brimme of the water, (for Iordan ouerfloweth all his banks at the time of haruest)
\v 16 That the waters which came downe from aboue, stood \add and\add* rose vp vpon an heape very farre, from the city Adam, that \add is\add* beside Zaretan: and those that came downe toward the sea of the plaine, \add euen\add* the salt sea, failed, \add and\add* were cut off: and the people passed ouer right against Iericho.
\v 17 And the Priestes that bare the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, stood firme on drie ground, in the midst of Iordan, and all the Israelites passed ouer on drie ground, vntill all the people were passed cleane ouer Iordan.
\c 4
\v 0 1 Twelue men are appointed to take twelue stones for a memoriall out of Iordan. 9 Twelue other stones are set vp in the middest of Iordan. 10. 19 The people passe ouer. 14 God magnifieth Ioshua. 20 The twelue stones are pitched in Gilgal.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 4:1 \ft Deut. 27. 2.\f*\f + \fr 4:1 \ft Chap.3. 12.\f*And it came to passe when all the people were cleane passed ouer Iordan, that the \nd LORD\nd* spake vnto Ioshua, saying,
\v 2 Take you twelue men out of the people, out of euery tribe a man,
\v 3 And command you them, saying, Take you hence out of the mids of Iordan, out of the place where the Priests feet stood firme, twelue stones, and yee shal cary them ouer with you, and leaue them in the lodging place where you shall lodge this night.
\v 4 Then Ioshua called the twelue men, whom he had prepared of the children of Israel, out of euery tribe a man:
\v 5 And Ioshua said vnto them, Passe ouer before the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd* your God into the mids of Iordan, and take ye vp euery man of you a stone vpon his shoulder, according vnto the number of the tribes of the children of Israel:
\v 6 \f + \fr 4:6 \ft Heb. to morrow.\f*That this may be a signe among you, \add that\add* when your children aske \add their fathers\add* in time to come, saying, What meane you by these stones?
\v 7 Then yee shall answere them, That the waters of Iordan were cut off before the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, when it passed ouer Iordan, the waters of Iordan were cut off: and these stones shall bee for a memoriall vnto the children of Israel for euer.
\v 8 And the children of Israel did so as Ioshua commanded, and tooke vp twelue stones out of the midst of Iordan, as the \nd LORD\nd* spake vnto Ioshua, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel, and caried them ouer with them, vnto the place where they lodged, and laid them downe there.
\v 9 And Ioshua set vp twelue stones in the midst of Iordan, in the place where the feet of the Priests which bare the Arke of the Couenant, stood: and they are there vnto this day.
\v 10 ¶ For the Priests which bare the Arke, stood in the midst of Iordan, vntill euery thing was finished that the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Ioshua to speake vnto the people, according to all that Moses commanded Ioshua: and the people hasted and passed ouer.
\v 11 And it came to passe when all the people were cleane passed ouer, that the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd* passed ouer, and the Priests in the presence of the people.
\v 12 \f + \fr 4:12 \ft Num. 32. 27.\f*And the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad, and halfe the tribe of Manasseh, passed ouer armed before the children of Israel, as Moses spake vnto them:
\v 13 \f + \fr 4:13 \ft Or. ready armed.\f*About fourty thousand prepared for war, passed ouer before the \nd LORD\nd* vnto battell, to the plaines of Iericho.
\v 14 ¶ On that day the \nd LORD\nd* magnified Ioshua in the sight of all Israel, and they feared him, as they feared Moses all the dayes of his life.
\v 15 And the \nd LORD\nd* spake vnto Ioshua, saying,
\v 16 Command the Priests that beare the Arke of the Testimony, that they come vp out of Iordan.
\v 17 Ioshua therefore commaunded the Priests, saying, Come yee vp out of Iordan.
\v 18 \f + \fr 4:18 \ft Hebr. plucked vp.\f*\f + \fr 4:18 \ft Hebr. went.\f*And it came to passe when the Priests that bare the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, were come vp out of the mids of Iordan, \add and\add* the soles of the Priests feete were lift vp vnto the dry land, that the waters of Iordan returned vnto their place, and flowed ouer all his banks, as \add they did\add* before.
\v 19 ¶ And the people came vp out of Iordan on the tenth \add day\add* of the first moneth, and encamped in Gilgal, in the East border of Iericho.
\v 20 And those twelue stones which they tooke out of Iordan, did Ioshua pitch in Gilgal.
\v 21 \f + \fr 4:21 \ft Hebr. to morrow.\f*And he spake vnto the children of Israel, saying, When your children shal aske their fathers in time to come, saying, What meane these stones?
\v 22 Then yee shall let your children know, saying, Israel came ouer this Iordan on dry land.
\v 23 \f + \fr 4:23 \ft Exod. 14. 21.\f*For the \nd LORD\nd* your God dried vp the waters of Iordan from before you, vntill yee were passed ouer, as the \nd LORD\nd* your God did to the Red sea, which hee dried vp from before vs, vntill we were gone ouer:
\v 24 \f + \fr 4:24 \ft Hebr. all dayes.\f*That all the people of the earth might know the hand of the \nd LORD\nd*, that it \add is\add* mighty, that ye might feare the \nd LORD\nd* your God for euer.
\c 5
\v 0 1 The Canaanites are afraid. 2 Ioshua renueth Circumcision. 10 The Passeouer is kept at Gilgal. 12 Manna ceaseth. 13 An Angel appeareth to Ioshua.
\v 1 ¶ And it came to passe when all the Kings of the Amorites which \add were\add* on the side of Iordan Westward, and all the Kings of the Canaanites, which \add were\add* by the Sea, heard that the \nd LORD\nd* had dried vp the waters of Iordan from before the children of Israel, vntill we were passed ouer, that their heart melted; neither was there spirit in them any more, because of the children of Israel.
\v 2 ¶ \f + \fr 5:2 \ft Exod.4. 25.\f*\f + \fr 5:2 \ft Or, kniues of flints.\f*At that time the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Ioshua, Make thee sharpe kniues, and circumcise againe the children of Israel the second time.
\v 3 \f + \fr 5:3 \ft Or, Gibeah-haaraloth.\f*And Ioshua made him sharpe kniues, and circumcised the children of Israel at the hill of the foreskinnes.
\v 4 And this \add is\add* the cause why Ioshua did circumcise: all the people that came out of Egypt, \add that were\add* males, \add euen\add* all the men of warre, died in the wildernes by the way after they came out of Egypt.
\v 5 Now all the people that came out, were circumcised, but all the people \add that were\add* borne in the wildernesse by the way, as they came foorth out of Egypt, \add them\add* they had not circumcised.
\v 6 \f + \fr 5:6 \ft Num.14 23.\f*For the children of Israel walked fourtie yeeres in the wildernesse, till all the people \add that were\add* men of warre which came out of Egypt were consumed, because they obeyed not the voyce of the \nd LORD\nd*, vnto whome the \nd LORD\nd* sware that hee would not shew them the land which the \nd LORD\nd* sware vnto their fathers, that he would giue vs, a land that floweth with milke & honie.
\v 7 And their children, \add whom\add* hee raised vp in their stead, them Ioshua circumcised, for they were vncircumcised: because they had not circumcised them by the way.
\v 8 \f + \fr 5:8 \ft Heb. when the people had made an end to be circumcised.\f*And it came to passe when they had done circumcising all the people, that they abode in their places in the campe, till they were whole.
\v 9 \f + \fr 5:9 \ft i. rolling.\f*And the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto Ioshua, This day haue I rolled away the reproch of Egypt from off you: Wherefore the name of the place is called Gilgal vnto this day.
\v 10 ¶ And the children of Israel incamped in Gilgal, and kept the Passeouer, on the fourteenth day of the moneth at euen, in the plaines of Iericho.
\v 11 And they did eate of the olde corne of the land, on the morrow after the Passeouer, vnleauened cakes, and parched corne in the selfe same day.
\v 12 ¶ And the Manna ceased on the morrow after they had eaten of the old corne of the land, neither had the children of Israel Manna any more, but they did eate of the fruit of the land of Canaan that yeere.
\v 13 ¶ \f + \fr 5:13 \ft Exod. 23. 23.\f*And it came to passe when Ioshua was by Iericho, that he lift vp his eyes, and looked, and beholde, there stood a man ouer against him, with his sword dawen in his hand: and Ioshua went vnto him, and said vnto him, \add Art\add* thou for vs, or for our aduersaries?
\v 14 \f + \fr 5:14 \ft Or, Prince.\f*And he said, Nay, but \add as\add* captaine of the hoste of the \nd LORD\nd* am I now come. And Ioshua fell on his face to the earth, and did worship, and said vnto him, What saith my \nd LORD\nd* vnto his seruant?
\v 15 \f + \fr 5:15 \ft Exod.3.9. acts.7.33.\f*And the captaine of the \nd LORD\nd*s hoste said vnto Ioshua, Loose thy shooe from off thy foote, for the place whereon thou standest, \add is\add* holy: And Ioshua did so.
\c 6
\v 0 1 Iericho is shut vp. 2 God instructeth Ioshua how to besiege it. 12 The citie is compassed. 17 It must be accursed. 20 The walles fall downe. 22 Rahab is saued. 26 The builder of Iericho is cursed.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 6:1 \ft Hebr. did shut vp, and was shut vp.\f*Now Iericho was straitly shut vp, because of the children of Israel: none went out, & none came in.
\v 2 And the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Ioshua, See, I haue giuen into thine hand Iericho, and the King thereof, \add and\add* the mighty men of valour.
\v 3 And ye shall compasse the city, all yee men of warre, \add and\add* goe round about the city once: thus shalt thou doe sixe dayes.
\v 4 And seuen Priests shall beare before the Arke seuen trumpets of rams hornes: and the seuenth day yee shall compasse the city seuen times, and the Priests shall blow with the trumpets.
\v 5 \f + \fr 6:5 \ft Hebr. vnder it.\f*And it shall come to passe that when they make a long \add blast\add* with the rammes-horne, \add and\add* when ye heare the sound of the trumpet, all the people shall shout with a great shout: and the wall of the citie shall fall downe flat, and the people shall ascend vp euery man straight before him.
\v 6 ¶ And Ioshua the sonne of Nun called the Priests, and said vnto them, Take vp the Arke of the Couenant, and let seuen Priests beare seuen trumpets of rammes-hornes, before the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 7 And he said vnto the people, Passe on, and compasse the city, and let him that is armed passe on before the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 8 ¶ And it came to passe when Ioshua had spoken vnto the people, that the seuen Priestes bearing the seuen trumpets of rammes hornes, passed on before the \nd LORD\nd*, and blew with the trumpets: and the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd* followed them.
\v 9 ¶ \f + \fr 6:9 \ft Heb. gathering host\f*And the armed men went before the Priests that blew with the trumpets: and the rereward came after the Arke, the Priests going on, and blowing with the trumpets.
\v 10 \f + \fr 6:10 \ft Heb. make your voyce to be heard.\f*And Ioshua had commanded the people, saying, Ye shall not shout, nor make any noise with your voice, neither shall \add any\add* word proceed out of your mouth, vntill the day I bid you shoute, then shall ye shoute.
\v 11 So the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd* compassed the citie, going about \add it\add* once: and they came into the campe, and lodged in the campe.
\v 12 ¶ And Ioshua rose earely in the morning, and the Priests tooke vp the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 13 And seuen Priests bearing seuen trumpets of rammes hornes before the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*, went on continually, and blew with the trumpets: and the armed men went before them, but the rereward came after the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*, the Priests going on and blowing with the trumpets.
\v 14 And the second day they compassed the citie once, and returned into the campe: so they did sixe dayes.
\v 15 And it came to passe on the seuenth day, that they rose early about the dawning of the day, and compassed the citie after the same maner, seuen times: only on that day they compassed the citie seuen times.
\v 16 And it came to passe at the seuenth time, when the Priests blewe with the trumpets, Ioshua said vnto the people, Shout, for the \nd LORD\nd* hath giuen you the citie.
\v 17 ¶ \f + \fr 6:17 \ft Or, deuoted.\f*\f + \fr 6:17 \ft Chap.2.4\f*And the citie shalbe accursed, \add euen\add* it, and all that \add are\add* therein, to the \nd LORD\nd*: onely Rahab the harlot shal liue, she, and all that \add are\add* with her in the house, because she hid the messengers that we sent.
\v 18 And you, in any wise keepe your selues from the accursed thing, lest yee make your selues accursed, when yee take of the accursed thing, and make the campe of Israel a curse, and trouble it.
\v 19 \f + \fr 6:19 \ft Hebr. holinesse.\f*But all the siluer, and gold, and vessels of brasse and yron, \add are\add* consecrated vnto the \nd LORD\nd*: they shall come into the treasurie of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 20 \f + \fr 6:20 \ft Heb.11. 30.\f*\f + \fr 6:20 \ft Hebr. vnder it.\f*So the people shouted when the Priests blew with the trumpets: and it came to passe when the people heard the sound of the trumpet, and the people shouted with a great shout, that the wall fell downe flat, so that the people went vp into the citie, euery man straight before him, and they tooke the citie.
\v 21 And they vtterly destroyed all that \add was\add* in the city, both man and woman, yong and old, and oxe, and sheepe, and asse, with the edge of the sword.
\v 22 \f + \fr 6:22 \ft Chap.2. 14. Heb.11. 31.\f*But Ioshua had said vnto the two men that had spied out the countrey; Goe into the harlots house, and bring out thence the woman and all that she hath, as ye sware vnto her.
\v 23 \f + \fr 6:23 \ft Hebr. families.\f*And the yong men that were spies, went in, and brought out Rahab, and her father, and her mother, and her brethren, and all that she had: and they brought out all her kinred, and left them without the campe of Israel.
\v 24 And they burnt the city with fire, and all that \add was\add* therein: onely the siluer & the gold, and the vessels of brasse and of yron, they put into the Treasury of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 25 And Ioshua saued Rahab the harlot aliue, and her fathers houshold, and all that she had: and she dwelleth in Israel \add euen\add* vnto this day, because she hid the messengers which Ioshua sent to spy out Iericho.
\v 26 ¶ \f + \fr 6:26 \ft 1.King. 16.34.\f*And Ioshua adiured \add them\add* at that time, saying, Cursed \add be\add* the man before the \nd LORD\nd*, that riseth vp and buildeth this city Iericho: he shall lay the foundation therof in his first borne, and in his yongest sonne shall hee set vp the gates of it.
\v 27 So the \nd LORD\nd* was with Ioshua, and his fame was \add noised\add* throughout all the countrey.
\c 7
\v 0 1 The Israelites are smitten at Ai. 6 Ioshuas complaint. 10 God instructeth him what to doe. 16 Achan is taken by the Lot. 19 His confession. 22 Hee and all he had are destroyed in the valley of Achor.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 7:1 \ft Chap.22. 20. 1.chron. 2.7.\f*But the children of Israel committed a trespasse in the accursed thing: for Achan the sonne of Carmi, the sonne of Zabdi, the sonne of Zerah, of the tribe of Iudah, tooke of the accursed thing: and the anger of the \nd LORD\nd* was kindled against the children of Israel.
\v 2 And Ioshua sent men from Iericho to Ai, which \add is\add* beside Beth-auen, on the East side of Bethel, and spake vnto them, saying, Goe vp and view the countrey. And the men went vp, and viewed Ai.
\v 3 \f + \fr 7:3 \ft Heb. about 2000.men: or, about 3000.men.\f*And they returned to Ioshua, and said vnto him, Let not all the people goe vp: but let about two or three thousand men goe vp, and smite Ai, \add and\add* make not all the people to labour thither, for they \add are but\add* few.
\v 4 So there went vp thither of the people about three thousand men, and they fled before the men of Ai.
\v 5 \f + \fr 7:5 \ft Or, in Morad.\f*And the men of Ai smote of them about thirty and sixe men: for they chased them \add from\add* before the gate \add euen\add* vnto Shebarim, and smote them in the going downe: Wherefore the hearts of the people melted, & became as water.
\v 6 ¶ And Ioshua rent his clothes, and fell to the earth vpon his face, before the Arke of the \nd LORD\nd*, vntill the euentide, he and the Elders of Israel, and put dust vpon their heads.
\v 7 And Ioshua said, Alas, O \nd LORD\nd* God, wherefore hast thou at all brought this people ouer Iordan, to deliuer vs into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy vs? Would to God we had bene content, and dwelt on the other side Iordan.
\v 8 \f + \fr 7:8 \ft Hebr. neckes.\f*Oh \nd LORD\nd*! what shall I say, when Israel turneth their backes before their enemies?
\v 9 For the Canaanites, and all the inhabitants of the land shall heare \add of it\add*, and shall enuiron vs round, and cut off our name from the earth: and what wilt thou doe vnto thy great Name?
\v 10 ¶ \f + \fr 7:10 \ft Heb. fallest.\f*And the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto Ioshua, Get thee vp; wherefore liest thou thus vpon thy face?
\v 11 Israel hath sinned, and they haue also transgressed my Couenant which I commaunded them: for they haue euen taken of the accursed thing, and haue also stollen, and dissembled also, and they haue put \add it\add* euen amongst their owne stuffe.
\v 12 Therefore the children of Israel could not stand before their enemies, \add but\add* turned \add their\add* backs before their enemies, because they were accursed: neither will I bee with you any more, except yee destroy the accursed from amongst you.
\v 13 Up, sanctifie the people, and say, Sanctifie your selues against to morrow: for thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel, \add There is\add* an accursed thing in the midst of thee, O Israel: thou canst not stand before thine enemies, vntill ye take away the accursed thing from among you.
\v 14 In the morning therefore ye shal be brought, according to your tribes: and it shall be \add that\add* the tribe which the \nd LORD\nd* taketh, shall come according to the families \add thereof\add*, and the familie which the \nd LORD\nd* shall take, shal come by housholdes: and the housholdes which the \nd LORD\nd* shall take, shal come man by man.
\v 15 \f + \fr 7:15 \ft Or, wickednesse.\f*And it shalbe that he \add that\add* is taken with the accursed thing, shall bee burnt with fire, he, and all that hee hath: because he hath transgressed the couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, and because hee hath wrought folly in Israel.
\v 16 ¶ So Ioshua rose vp earely in the morning, and brought Israel by their tribes, and the tribe of Iudah was taken.
\v 17 And hee brought the familie of Iudah, and he tooke the familie of the Zarhites: and he brought the familie of the Zarhites, man by man, and Zabdi was taken.
\v 18 And hee brought his houshold, man by man, and Achan the sonne of Carmi, the sonne of Zabdi, the sonne of Zerah, of the tribe of Iudah, was taken.
\v 19 And Ioshua said vnto Achan, My sonne, giue, I pray thee, glory to the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel, and make confession vnto him, and tel me now, what thou hast done, hide \add it\add* not from me.
\v 20 And Achan answered Ioshua, and said, Indeed I haue sinned against the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel, and thus and thus haue I done.
\v 21 \f + \fr 7:21 \ft Heb. tongue\f*When I saw among the spoiles a goodly Babylonish garment, and two hundred shekels of siluer, and a wedge of gold of fiftie shekels weight, then I coueted them, and tooke them, and behold, they \add are\add* hid in the earth in the midst of my tent, and the siluer vnder it.
\v 22 ¶ So Ioshua sent messengers, and they ran vnto the tent, and behold, \add it was\add* hid in his tent, and the siluer vnder it.
\v 23 \f + \fr 7:23 \ft Heb. powred.\f*And they tooke them out of the midst of the tent, and brought them vnto Ioshua, and vnto all the children of Israel, and laid them out before the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 24 And Ioshua and all Israel with him tooke Achan the sonne of Zerah, and the siluer, and the garment, and the wedge of golde, and his sonnes, and his daughters, and his oxen, and his asses, and his sheepe, and his tent, and all that he had: and they brought them vnto the valley of Achor.
\v 25 And Ioshua said, Why hast thou troubled vs? the \nd LORD\nd* shall trouble thee this day. And all Israel stoned him with stones, and burned them with fire, after they had stoned them with stones.
\v 26 \f + \fr 7:26 \ft That is, trouble.\f*And they raised ouer him a great heape of stones vnto this day: so the \nd LORD\nd* turned from the fiercenesse of his anger: Wherefore the name of the place was called, The valley of Achor, vnto this day.
\c 8
\v 0 1 God incourageth Ioshua. 3 The stratageme whereby Ai was taken. 29 The king thereof is hanged. 30 Ioshua buildeth an Altar, 32 writeth the Lawe on stones, 33 propoundeth blessings and cursings.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 8:1 \ft Deut.1. 21. & 7.18.\f*And the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Ioshua, Feare not, neither be thou dismaid: take all the people of warre with thee, and arise, goe vp to Ai: See, I haue giuen into thy hand the king of Ai, and his people, and his citie, and his land.
\v 2 \f + \fr 8:2 \ft Chap.6.21\f*\f + \fr 8:2 \ft Deut.20 14.\f*And thou shalt doe to Ai and her king, as thou diddest vnto Iericho and her king: Onely the spoile thereof and the cattell thereof shall ye take for a pray vnto your selues: lay thee an ambush for the citie, behind it.
\v 3 ¶ So Ioshua arose, and all the people of warre, to goe vp against Ai: and Ioshua chose out thirtie thousand mighty men of valour, and sent them away by night:
\v 4 And he commanded them, saying, Behold, ye shall lie in wait against the citie, \add euen\add* behind the citie: goe not very farre from the citie, but be ye all ready:
\v 5 And I, and all the people that \add are\add* with mee, will approch vnto the citie: and it shall come to passe when they come out against vs, as at the first, that we will flee before them,
\v 6 \f + \fr 8:6 \ft Hebr. pulled.\f*(For they will come out after vs) till we haue drawen them from the citie; for they will say, They flee before vs, as at the first: therefore we will flee before them.
\v 7 Then yee shall rise vp from the ambush, and seise vpon the citie: for the \nd LORD\nd* your God will deliuer it into your hand.
\v 8 And it shall be when yee haue taken the citie, \add that\add* ye shall set the citie on fire: according to the commandement of the \nd LORD\nd* shall ye do. See, I haue commanded you.
\v 9 ¶ Ioshua therefore sent them foorth, and they went to lie in ambush, and abode betweene Bethel and Ai, on the West side of Ai: but Ioshua lodged that night among the people.
\v 10 And Ioshua rose vp early in the morning, and numbred the people, and went vp; he, and the Elders of Israel, before the people to Ai.
\v 11 And all the people, \add euen the people\add* of warre that \add were\add* with him, went vp, and drew nigh, and came before the city, and pitched on the North side of Ai: now \add there was\add* a valley betweene them and Ai.
\v 12 \f + \fr 8:12 \ft Or, of Ai.\f*And he tooke about fiue thousand men, and set them to lye in ambush betweene Bethel and Ai, on the West side of the citie.
\v 13 \f + \fr 8:13 \ft Hebr. their lying in wait.\f*And when they had set the people, \add euen\add* all the hoste that \add was\add* on the North of the city, and their liers in wait on the West of the citie: Ioshua went that night into the midst of the valley.
\v 14 ¶ And it came to passe when the King of Ai saw \add it\add*, that they hasted, and rose vp early, and the men of the citie went out against Israel to battell, hee, and all his people, at a time appointed, before the plaine, but hee wist not that \add there were\add* liers in ambush against him behind the city.
\v 15 And Ioshua and all Israel made as if they were beaten before them, and fled by the way of the wildernesse.
\v 16 And all the people that \add were\add* in Ai, were called together to pursue after them: and they pursued after Ioshua, and were drawen away from the city.
\v 17 And there was not a man left in Ai or Bethel, that went not out after Israel: and they left the citie open, and pursued after Israel.
\v 18 And the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Ioshua, Stretch out the speare that \add is\add* in thy hand, toward Ai; for I will giue it into thine hand. And Ioshua stretched out the speare that hee had in his hand, toward the city.
\v 19 And the ambush arose quickly out of their place, and they ranne as soone as he had stretched out his hand: and they entred into the city, and tooke it, and hasted, and set the citie on fire.
\v 20 \f + \fr 8:20 \ft Heb. hand.\f*And when the men of Ai looked behind them, they saw, and behold, the smoke of the city ascended vp to heauen, and they had no power to flee this way or that way: and the people that fled to the wildernesse, turned backe vpon the pursuers.
\v 21 And when Ioshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had taken the city, and that the smoke of the city ascended, then they turned againe and slew the men of Ai.
\v 22 \f + \fr 8:22 \ft Deut.7 2.\f*And the other issued out of the citie against them, so they were in the midst of Israel; some on this side, and some on that side, and they smote them; so that they let none of them remaine or escape.
\v 23 And the King of Ai they tooke aliue, and brought him to Ioshua.
\v 24 And it came to passe when Israel had made an end of slaying all the inhabitants of Ai, in the field, in the wildernesse wherein they chased them, and when they were all fallen on the edge of the sword, vntill they were consumed, that all the Israelites returned vnto Ai, and smote it with the edge of the sword.
\v 25 And \add so\add* it was \add that\add* all that fell that day, both of men and women, \add were\add* twelue thousand, \add euen\add* all the men of Ai.
\v 26 For Ioshua drew not his hand backe wherewith hee stretched out the speare, vntill he had vtterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai.
\v 27 \f + \fr 8:27 \ft Num.31. 22, 26.\f*\f + \fr 8:27 \ft Verse 2.\f*Onely the cattell, and the spoile of that city Israel tooke for a pray vnto themselues, according vnto the word of the \nd LORD\nd*, which he commaunded Ioshua.
\v 28 And Ioshua burnt Ai, and made it an heape for euer, \add euen\add* a desolation vnto this day.
\v 29 \f + \fr 8:29 \ft Chap.7. 25.\f*And the king of Ai he hanged on a tree vntil euentide: and assoone as the sunne was downe, Ioshua commaunded that they should take his carkeise downe from the tree, and cast it at the entring of the gate of the citie, and raise thereon a great heape of stones \add that remaineth\add* vnto this day.
\v 30 ¶ Then Ioshua built an Altar vnto the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel in mount Ebal,
\v 31 \f + \fr 8:31 \ft Exod. 20. 25. deut. 27.5.\f*As Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* commaunded the children of Israel, as it is written in the booke of the Law of Moses, an Altar of whole stones, ouer which no man hath lift vp \add any\add* yron: and they offred theron burnt offerings vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, and sacrificed peace offerings.
\v 32 ¶ And he wrote there vpon the stones a copie of the Lawe of Moses, which hee wrote in the presence of the children of Israel.
\v 33 \f + \fr 8:33 \ft Deut. 11. 29. & 27.12\f*And all Israel, and their Elders, and Officers, and their Iudges, stood on this side the Arke, and on that side, before the Priests the Leuites, which bare the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, aswell the stranger, as he that was borne among them: halfe of them ouer against mount Gerizim, and halfe of them ouer against mount Ebal, as Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* had commanded before, that they should blesse the people of Israel.
\v 34 And afterward hee read all the words of the Law, the blessings and cursings, according to all that is written in the booke of the Law.
\v 35 \f + \fr 8:35 \ft Deut. 31. 12.\f*\f + \fr 8:35 \ft Hebr. walked.\f*There was not a word of all that Moses commanded, which Ioshua read not before all the Congregation of Israel, with the women and the litle ones, and the strangers that were conuersant among them.
\c 9
\v 0 1 The kings combine against Israel. 3 The Gibeonites by craft obtaine a League. 16 For which they are condemned to perpetual bondage.
\v 1 ¶ And it came to passe when all the kings which \add were\add* on this side Iordan in the hilles, and in the valleys, and in all the coasts of the great sea, ouer against Lebanon, the Hittite, and the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hiuite, and the Iebusite heard \add thereof\add*:
\v 2 \f + \fr 9:2 \ft Heb. mouth\f*That they gathered themselues together to fight with Ioshua, and with Israel, with one accord.
\v 3 ¶ And when the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Ioshua had done vnto Iericho, and to Ai,
\v 4 They did worke wilily, and went and made as if they had beene embassadours, and tooke old sackes vpon their asses, and wine-bottels, old, and rent, and bound vp,
\v 5 And old shooes and clowted vpon their feet, & olde garments vpon them, and all the bread of their prouision was drie \add and\add* mouldie.
\v 6 And they went to Ioshua vnto the campe at Gilgal, and said vnto him, and to the men of Israel, Wee be come from a farre countrey: Now therefore make ye a league with vs.
\v 7 And the men of Israel said vnto the Hiuites, Peraduenture yee dwell among vs, and how shall wee make a league with you.?
\v 8 And they said vnto Ioshua, Wee \add are\add* thy seruants. And Ioshua said vnto them, Who \add are\add* ye? And from whence come ye?
\v 9 And they said vnto him, From a very farre countrey thy seruants are come, because of the Name of the \nd LORD\nd* thy God: for wee haue heard the fame of him, and all that hee did in Egypt,
\v 10 And all that hee did to the two kings of the Amorites, that \add were\add* beyond Iordan, to Sihon king of Heshbon, and to Og king of Bashan, which \add was\add* at Ashtaroth.
\v 11 \f + \fr 9:11 \ft Hebr. in your hand.\f*Wherefore our Elders and all the inhabitants of our countrey, spake to vs, saying, Take victuals with you for the iourney, and goe to meete them, and say vnto them, Wee \add are\add* your seruants: therefore now make ye a league with vs.
\v 12 This our bread, wee tooke hote \add for\add* our prouision out of our houses, on the day we came forth to goe vnto you: but now behold, it is dry, & it is mouldy.
\v 13 And these bottels of wine which we filled, \add were\add* new, and behold, they be rent: and these our garments, and our shooes are become old, by reason of the very long iourney.
\v 14 \f + \fr 9:14 \ft Or, they receiued the men by reason of their victuals.\f*And the men tooke of their victuals, and asked not counsell at the mouth of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 15 And Ioshua made peace with them, and made a league with them, to let them liue: and the princes of the Congregation sware vnto them.
\v 16 ¶ And it came to passe at the end of three dayes, after they had made a league with them, that they heard that they \add were\add* their neighbours, and \add that\add* they dwelt among them.
\v 17 And the children of Israel iourneyed, and came vnto their cities on the third day: now their cities \add were\add* Gibeon, and Chephirah, and Beeroth, and Kiriath iearim.
\v 18 And the children of Israel smote them not, because the Princes of the Congregation had sworne vnto them by the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel: And all the Congregation murmured against the Princes.
\v 19 But all the Princes said vnto all the Congregation, We haue sworne vnto them by the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel: now therefore we may not touch them.
\v 20 This we will doe to them; wee will euen let them liue, lest wrath be vpon vs, because of the oath which wee sware vnto them.
\v 21 \f + \fr 9:21 \ft Verse 15.\f*And the Princes said vnto them, Let them liue, (but let them bee hewers of wood, and drawers of water, vnto all the Congregation,) as the Princes had promised them.
\v 22 ¶ And Ioshua called for them, and he spake vnto them, saying, Wherefore haue ye beguiled vs, saying, We \add are\add* very farre from you? when ye dwell among vs.
\v 23 \f + \fr 9:23 \ft Hebr. not be cut off from you.\f*Now therefore ye \add are\add* cursed, and there shall none of you bee freed from being bondmen, and hewers of wood, and drawers of water, for the house of my God.
\v 24 \f + \fr 9:24 \ft Deut.7.1.\f*And they answered Ioshua, and said, Because it was certainely told thy seruants, how that the \nd LORD\nd* thy God commanded his seruant Moses to giue you all the land, and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land from before you, therefore we were sore afraid of our liues because of you, and haue done this thing.
\v 25 And now behold, we \add are\add* in thine hand: as it seemeth good and right vnto thee to doe vnto vs, doe.
\v 26 And so did he vnto them, and deliuered them out of the hand of the children of Israel, that they slew them not.
\v 27 And Ioshua made them that day, hewers of wood, and drawers of water for the Congregation, and for the Altar of the \nd LORD\nd*, euen vnto this day, in the place which he should choose.
\c 10
\v 0 1 Fiue Kings warre against Gibeon. 6 Ioshua rescueth it. 10 God fighteth against them with hailestones. 12 The Sunne and Moone stand still at the word of Ioshua. 16 The fiue Kings are mured in a caue. 21 They are brought forth, 24 scornefully vsed, 26 and hanged. 28 Seuen Kings more are conquered. 43 Ioshua returneth to Gilgal.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 10:1 \ft Chap.6. 15.\f*\f + \fr 10:1 \ft Chap. 8.3.\f*Now it came to passe when Adoni-zedek King of Ierusalem, had heard how Ioshua had taken Ai, and had vtterly destroyed it, ( as he had done to Iericho, and her King, so hee had done to Ai, and her King) and how the inhabitants of Gibeon had made peace with Israel, and were among them,
\v 2 \f + \fr 10:2 \ft Hebr. cities of the kingdome.\f*That they feared greatly because Gibeon \add was\add* a great citie, as one of the royall cities, and because it \add was\add* greater then Ai, and all the men thereof \add were\add* mighty.
\v 3 Wherefore Adoni-zedek King of Ierusalem, sent vnto Hoham King of Hebron, and vnto Piram, king of Iarmuth, and vnto Iaphia king of Lachish, and vnto Debir king of Eglon, saying,
\v 4 Come vp vnto me, and helpe me, that we may smite Gibeon: for it hath made peace with Ioshua, and with the children of Israel.
\v 5 Therefore the fiue Kings of the Amorites, the king of Ierusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Iarmuth, the king of Lachish, the king of Eglon, gathered themselues together, and went vp, they, and all their hostes, and encamped before Gibeon, and made warre against it.
\v 6 ¶ And the men of Gibeon sent vnto Ioshua to the campe to Gilgal, saying, Slacke not thy hand from thy seruants, come vp to vs quickly, and saue vs, and helpe vs: for all the kings of the Amorites that dwell in the mountaines, are gathered together against vs.
\v 7 So Ioshua ascended from Gilgal, he, and all the people of warre with him, and all the mighty men of valour.
\v 8 ¶ And the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Ioshua, Feare them not: for I haue deliuered them into thine hand; there shall not a man of them stand before thee.
\v 9 Ioshua therefore came vnto them suddenly, and went vp from Gilgal all night.
\v 10 And the \nd LORD\nd* discomfited them before Israel, and slewe them with a great slaughter at Gibeon, and chased them along the way that goeth vp to Bethoron, and smote them to Azekah and vnto Makkedah.
\v 11 And it came to passe as they fled from before Israel, \add and\add* were in the going downe to Bethoron, that the \nd LORD\nd* cast downe great stones from heauen vpon them, vnto Azekah, and they died: \add they were\add* moe which died with hailestones, then \add they\add* whome the children of Israel slew with the sword.
\v 12 ¶ \f + \fr 10:12 \ft Esa.28.21 ecclus.46.4\f*\f + \fr 10:12 \ft Heb. bee silent.\f*Then spake Ioshua to the \nd LORD\nd* in the day when the \nd LORD\nd* deliuered vp the Amorites before the children of Israel, and hee said in the sight of Israel, Sunne, stand thou still vpon Gibeon, and thou Moone in the valley of Aialon.
\v 13 \f + \fr 10:13 \ft Or, the vpright?\f*And the Sunne stood still, and the Moone stayed, vntill the people had auenged themselues vpon their enemies. \add Is\add* not this written in the booke of Iasher? So the Sunne stood still in the midst of heauen, and hasted not to goe downe, about a whole day.
\v 14 And there was no day like that, before it, or after it, that the \nd LORD\nd* hearkened vnto the voyce of a man: for the \nd LORD\nd* fought for Israel.
\v 15 ¶ And Ioshua returned, and all Israel with him, vnto the campe to Gilgal.
\v 16 But these fiue kings fled, and hid themselues in a caue at Makkedah.
\v 17 And it was told Ioshua, saying, The fiue kings are found hid in a caue at Makkedah.
\v 18 And Ioshua said, Roule great stones vpon the mouth of the caue, and set men by it, for to keepe them.
\v 19 \f + \fr 10:19 \ft Heb. cut off the taile.\f*And stay you not, \add but\add* pursue after your enemies, and smite the hindmost of them, suffer them not to enter into their cities: for the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath deliuered them into your hand.
\v 20 And it came to passe when Ioshua and the children of Israel had made an end of slaying them with a very great slaughter, till they were consumed, that the rest \add which\add* remained of them, entred into fenced cities.
\v 21 And all the people returned to the campe to Ioshua at Makkedah in peace: none mooued his tongue against any of the children of Israel.
\v 22 Then said Ioshua, Open the mouth of the caue, and bring out those fiue kings vnto me out of the caue.
\v 23 And they did so, and brought forth those fiue kings vnto him out of the caue, the king of Ierusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Iarmuth, the king of Lachish, \add and\add* the king of Eglon.
\v 24 And it came to passe when they brought out those kings vnto Ioshua, that Ioshua called for all the men of Israel, and saide vnto the captaines of the men of war which went with him, Come neere, put your feete vpon the neckes of these kings. And they came neere, and put their feet vpon the necks of them.
\v 25 And Ioshua said vnto them, Feare not, nor be dismaid, bee strong, and of good courage: for thus shall the \nd LORD\nd* doe to all your enemies against whom ye fight.
\v 26 And afterward Ioshua smote them, and slew them, and hanged them on fiue trees: and they were hanging vpon the trees vntill the euening.
\v 27 \f + \fr 10:27 \ft Deut. 21. 23. chap. 8. 29.\f*And it came to passe at the time of the going downe of the Sunne, \add that\add* Ioshua commanded, and they tooke them downe off the trees, and cast them into the caue, wherein they had beene hid, and laid great stones in the caues mouth, \add which remain\add* vntil this very day.
\v 28 ¶ \f + \fr 10:28 \ft Chap. 6. 21.\f*And that day Ioshua tooke Makkedah, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and the king thereof hee vtterly destroyed, them, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein, he let none remaine: and he did to the king of Makkedah, as hee did vnto the king of Iericho.
\v 29 Then Ioshua passed from Makkedah, and all Israel with him, vnto Libnah, and fought against Libnah.
\v 30 And the \nd LORD\nd* deliuered it also and the king thereof, into the hand of Israel, and he smote it with the edge of the sword, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein: He let none remaine in it, but did vnto the king therof, as he did vnto the king of Iericho.
\v 31 ¶ And Ioshua passed from Libnah and all Israel with him, vnto Lachish, and encamped against it, and fought against it.
\v 32 And the \nd LORD\nd* deliuered Lachish into the hande of Israel, which tooke it on the second day, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein, according to all that he had done to Libnah.
\v 33 ¶ Then Horam king of Gezer, came vp to helpe Lachish, and Ioshua smote him and his people, vntill he had left him none remayning.
\v 34 ¶ And from Lachish, Ioshua passed vnto Eglon, and all Israel with him, and they encamped against it, and fought against it.
\v 35 And they tooke it on that day, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein he vtterly destroyed that day, according to all that he had done to Lachish.
\v 36 And Ioshua went vp from Eglon, and all Israel with him, vnto Hebron, and they fought against it.
\v 37 And they tooke it, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and the king thereof, and all the cities thereof, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein, he left none remaining, according to all that he had done to Eglon: but destroyed it vtterly, and all the soules that \add were\add* therein.
\v 38 ¶ And Ioshua returned, and all Israel with him to Debir, and fought against it.
\v 39 And hee tooke it, and the King thereof, and all the cities thereof, and they smote them with the edge of the sword, and vtterly destroyed all the soules that \add were\add* therein, he left none remayning: as he had done to Hebron, so he did to Debir, and to the king thereof, as he had done also to Libnah, and to her king.
\v 40 ¶ \f + \fr 10:40 \ft Deut. 26. 16,17.\f*So Ioshua smote all the countrey of the hils, and of the South, and of the vale, and of the springs, and all their kings, hee left none remayning, but vtterly destroyed all that breathed, as the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel commanded.
\v 41 And Ioshua smote them from Kadesh-Barnea, euen vnto Gaza, and all the countrey of Goshen, euen vnto Gibeon.
\v 42 And all these Kings and their land did Ioshua take at one time: because the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel fought for Israel.
\v 43 And Ioshua returned & al Israel with him, vnto the campe to Gilgal.
\c 11
\v 0 1 Diuers Kings ouercome at the waters of Merom. 10 Hazor is taken and burnt. 16 All the countrey taken by Ioshua. 21 The Anakims cut off.
\v 1 ¶ And it came to passe, when Iabin king of Hazor had heard \add those things\add*, that hee sent to Iobab king of Madon, and to the king of Shimron, & to the king of Achshaph,
\v 2 And to the kings that \add were\add* on the North of the mountaines, and of the plaines South of Cinneroth, and in the valley, and in the borders of Dor, on the West;
\v 3 \add And to\add* the Canaanite on the East and on the West, and \add to\add* the Amorite, and the Hittite, and the Perizzite, and the Iebusite in the mountaines, and \add to\add* the Hiuite vnder Hermon in the land of Mizpeh.
\v 4 And they went out, they and all their hostes with them, much people, euen as the sand that \add is\add* vpon the Seashore in multitude, with horses and charets very many.
\v 5 \f + \fr 11:5 \ft Hebr. assembled by appointment.\f*And when all these Kings were met together, they came and pitched together at the waters of Merom, to fight against Israel.
\v 6 ¶ And the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto Ioshua, Be not afraid because of them: for to morrow about this time will I deliuer them vp al slaine before Israel: thou shalt hough their horses, and burne their charets with fire.
\v 7 So Ioshua came, and all the people of warre with him, against them by the waters of Merom suddenly, and they fell vpon them.
\v 8 \f + \fr 11:8 \ft Or, Zidon-Rabbah.\f*\f + \fr 11:8 \ft Or, salt pits: Hebr. burning of waters.\f*And the \nd LORD\nd* deliuered them into the hand of Israel, who smote them, and chased them vnto great Zidon, and vnto Misrephothmaim, and vnto the valley of Mizpeh Eastward, and they smote them, vntill they left them none remayning.
\v 9 And Ioshua did vnto them as the \nd LORD\nd* bade him: hee houghed their horses, and burnt their charets with fire.
\v 10 ¶ And Ioshua at that time turned backe, and tooke Hazor, and smote the king thereof with the sword: for Hazor beforetime was the head of all those kingdomes.
\v 11 \f + \fr 11:11 \ft Hebr. any breath.\f*And they smote all the soules that \add were\add* therein with the edge of the sword, vtterly destroying \add them\add*: there was not any left to breathe; and he burnt Hazor with fire.
\v 12 \f + \fr 11:12 \ft Num.33. 52. deut. 7. 2. and 20, 16,17.\f*And all the cities of those kings, and all the kings of them, did Ioshua take, and smote them with the edge of the sword, \add and\add* he vtterly destroied them, as Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* commanded.
\v 13 \f + \fr 11:13 \ft Hebr. on their heape.\f*But \add as for\add* the cities \add that\add* stood still in their strength, Israel burned none of them, saue Hazor onely; that did Ioshua burne.
\v 14 And all the spoile of these cities, and the cattell, the children of Israel tooke for a pray vnto themselues: but euery man they smote with the edge of the sword, vntill they had destroyed them, neither left they any to breathe.
\v 15 ¶ \f + \fr 11:15 \ft Exod.34. 11.\f*\f + \fr 11:15 \ft Deut. 7.2\f*\f + \fr 11:15 \ft Heb. he remoued nothing.\f*As the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses his seruant, so did Moses command Ioshua, and so did Ioshua: hee left nothing vndone of all that the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses.
\v 16 So Ioshua tooke all that land, the hilles, and all the South countrey, and all the land of Goshen, and the valley, and the plaine, and the mountaine of Israel, and the valley of the same:
\v 17 \f + \fr 11:17 \ft Or, the smoothe mountaine.\f*Euen from the mount Halak, that goeth vp to Seir, vnto Baal-Gad, in the valley of Lebanon, vnder mount Hermon: and all their kings he tooke, and smote them, and slew them.
\v 18 Ioshua made warre a long time, with all those kings.
\v 19 \f + \fr 11:19 \ft Chap.9.3\f*There was not a citie that made peace with the children of Israel, saue the Hiuites the inhabitants of Gibeon; all \add other\add* they tooke in battell.
\v 20 For it was of the \nd LORD\nd* to harden their hearts, that they should come against Israel in battell, that he might destroy them vtterly, & that they might haue no fauour: but that hee might destroy them, as the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses.
\v 21 ¶ And at that time came Ioshua and cut off the Anakims from the mountaines, from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, and from all the mountaines of Iudah, and from all the mountaines of Israel: Ioshua destroyed them vtterly with their cities.
\v 22 There was none of the Anakims left in the land of the children of Israel: onely in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod, there remained.
\v 23 \f + \fr 11:23 \ft Numb.26 53.\f*So Ioshua tooke the whole land according to all that the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto Moses, and Ioshua gaue it for an inheritance vnto Israel, according to their diuisions by their tribes: and the land rested from warre.
\c 12
\v 0 1 The two kings whose countreys Moses tooke and disposed of. 7 The one and thirty kings on the other side Iordan which Ioshua smote.
\v 1 ¶ Now these \add are\add* the kings of the land, which the children of Israel smote, and possessed their land on the other side Iordan, toward the rising of the Sunne: from the riuer Arnon, vnto mount Hermon, and all the plaine on the East.
\v 2 \f + \fr 12:2 \ft Num. 21 24. deu.3.6\f*Sihon king of the Amorites who dwelt in Heshbon, \add and\add* ruled from Aroer, which \add is\add* vpon the banke of the riuer of Arnon, and from the middle of the riuer, and from halfe Gilead vnto the riuer Iabbok; \add which is\add* the border of the children of Ammon:
\v 3 \f + \fr 12:3 \ft Or, Teman\f*\f + \fr 12:3 \ft Or, the springs of Pisgah, or the hill.\f*\f + \fr 12:3 \ft Deut.3. 17. & 4.49.\f*And from the plaine, to the Sea of Cinneroth on the East, and vnto the sea of the plaine, \add euen\add* the salt sea on the East, the way to Beth-Ieshimoth: and from the South, vnder Ashdoth-Pisgah.
\v 4 ¶ \f + \fr 12:4 \ft Deut.3. 11. chap. 13.12.\f*And the coast of Og king of Bashan, \add which was\add* of the remnant of the Giants, that dwelt at Ashtaroth, and at Edrei,
\v 5 And reigned in mount Hermon, and in Salcah, and in all Bashan, vnto the border of the Geshurites, and the Maachathites, and halfe Gilead, the border of Sihon king of Heshbon.
\v 6 \f + \fr 12:6 \ft Num. 32. 29. deut. 3. 12. chap. 13.8.\f*Them did Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd*, and the children of Israel smite, and Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* gaue it \add for\add* a possession vnto the Reubenites, and Gadites, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh.
\v 7 ¶ \f + \fr 12:7 \ft Chap. 11. 17.\f*And these \add are\add* the kings of the countrey which Ioshua and the children of Israel smote on this side Iordan on the West, from Baal Gad in the valley of Lebanon, euen vnto the mount Halak, that goeth vp to Seir, which Ioshua gaue vnto the tribes of Israel \add for\add* a possession, according to their diuisions:
\v 8 In the mountaines and in the valleys, and in the plaines, and in the springs, and in the wildernesse, and in the South countrey: the Hittites, the Amorites, and the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hiuites, and the Iebusites.
\v 9 ¶ \f + \fr 12:9 \ft Chap. 6.2.\f*\f + \fr 12:9 \ft Chap. 8. 29.\f*The king of Iericho, one: the king of Ai, which \add is\add* beside Bethel, one:
\v 10 \f + \fr 12:10 \ft Chap. 10. 23.\f*The king of Ierusalem, one: the king of Hebron, one:
\v 11 The king of Iarmuth, one: the king of Lachis, one:
\v 12 \f + \fr 12:12 \ft Chap.10. 33.\f*The king of Eglon, one: the king of Gezer, one:
\v 13 \f + \fr 12:13 \ft Chap.10. 33.\f*The king of Debir, one: the king of Geder, one:
\v 14 The king of Hormah one: the king of Arad, one:
\v 15 \f + \fr 12:15 \ft Chap. 10. 29.\f*The king of Libnah, one: the king of Adullam, one:
\v 16 \f + \fr 12:16 \ft Chap. 10. 28.\f*The king of Makkedah, one: the king of Bethel, one:
\v 17 The king of Tappuah, one: the king of Hepher, one:
\v 18 \f + \fr 12:18 \ft Or, Saron.\f*The king of Aphek, one: the king of Lasharon, one:
\v 19 \f + \fr 12:19 \ft Chap. 11. 10.\f*The king of Madon, one: the king of Hazor, one:
\v 20 The king of Shimron-Meron, one: the king of Achshaph, one:
\v 21 The king of Taanach, one: the king of Megiddo, one:
\v 22 The king of Kedesh, one: the king of Iokneam of Carmel, one:
\v 23 \f + \fr 12:23 \ft Genes.14. 1.\f*The king of Dor, in the coast of Dor, one: the king of the nations of Gilgal, one:
\v 24 The king of Tirzah, one: all the kings thirtie and one.
\c 13
\v 0 1 The bounds of the land not yet conquered. 8 The inheritance of the two Tribes and halfe. 14. 33 The \nd LORD\nd* and his sacrifices, are the inheritance of Leui. 15 The bounds of the inheritance of Reuben. 22 Balaam slaine. 24 The bounds of the inheritance of Gad, 29 and of the halfe tribe of Manasseh.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 13:1 \ft Hebr. to possesse it.\f*Now Ioshua was old \add and\add* stricken in yeeres, \add and\add* the \nd LORD\nd* saide vnto him; Thou art old, and stricken in yeres, and there remaineth yet very much land to bee possessed.
\v 2 This \add is\add* the land that yet remaineth: all the borders of the Philistines, and all Geshuri,
\v 3 From Sihor, which \add is\add* before Egypt, euen vnto the borders of Ekron Northward, \add which\add* is counted to the Canaanite: fiue lords of the Philistines; the Gazathites, and the Ashdothites, the Eshkalonites, the Gittites, and the Ekronites; Also the Auites.
\v 4 \f + \fr 13:4 \ft Or, the caue.\f*From the South, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that \add is\add* beside the Sidonians, vnto Aphek, to the borders of the Amorites:
\v 5 And the land of the Giblites, and al Lebanon toward the Sunne rising, from Baal-Gad vnder mount Hermon, vnto the entring into Hamath.
\v 6 All the inhabitants of the hill countrey, from Lebanon vnto Misrephothmaim, \add and\add* all the Sidonians, them will I driue out from before the children of Israel: onely diuide thou it by lot vnto the Israelites, for an inheritance, as I haue commanded thee.
\v 7 Now therefore, diuide this land for an inheritance vnto the nine tribes, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh,
\v 8 \f + \fr 13:8 \ft Num. 32. 33. deut. 3. 13. chap.22 4.\f*With whom the Reubenites, and the Gadites haue receiued their inheritance, which Moses gaue them, beyond Iordan Eastward, \add euen\add* as Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* gaue them:
\v 9 From Aroer that \add is\add* vpon the banke of the riuer Arnon, and the citie that \add is\add* in the middest of the riuer, and all the plaine of Medeba vnto Dibon:
\v 10 And all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, which reigned in Heshbon, vnto the border of the children of Ammon:
\v 11 And Gilead, and the border of the Geshurites, and Maachathites, and all mount Hermon, and all Bashan vnto Salcah:
\v 12 \f + \fr 13:12 \ft Deut.3. 11. chap. 12.4.\f*All the kingdome of Og in Bashan, which reigned in Ashtaroth and in Edrei, who remained of the remnant of the giants: for these did Moses smite, and cast them out.
\v 13 Neuerthelesse, the children of Israel expelled not the Geshurites, nor the Maachathites: but the Geshurites and the Maachathites dwel among the Israelites vntill this day.
\v 14 Onely vnto the tribe of Leui hee gaue none inheritance: the sacrifices of the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel made by fire, \add are\add* their inheritance, as he said vnto them.
\v 15 ¶ And Moses gaue vnto the tribe of the children of Reuben \add inheritance\add* according to their families:
\v 16 And their coast was from Aroer that \add is\add* on the banke of the riuer Arnon, and the city that \add is\add* in the midst of the riuer, and all the plaine by Medeba.
\v 17 \f + \fr 13:17 \ft Or, the high places of Baal, and house of Baalmeon.\f*Heshbon and all her cities that \add are\add* in the plaine: Dibon, and Bamoth-Baal, and Beth-Baalmeon,
\v 18 And Iahazah, and Kedemoth, and Mephaath,
\v 19 And Kiriathaim, and Sibmah, and Zareth-shahar, in the mount of the valley,
\v 20 \f + \fr 13:20 \ft Deut. 3. 17.\f*\f + \fr 13:20 \ft Or, springs of Pisgah or the hill.\f*And Bethpeor, and Ashdoth-Pisgah, and Beth-ieshimoth:
\v 21 \f + \fr 13:21 \ft Num. 31. 8.\f*And all the cities of the plaine, and all the kingdome of Sihon king of the Amorites, which reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses smote with the princes of Midian, Eui, and Rekem, and Zur, and Hur, and Reba, \add which were\add* dukes of Sihon, dwelling in the countrey.
\v 22 ¶ \f + \fr 13:22 \ft Or, diuiner\f*Balaam also the sonne of Beor the Sooth-sayer did the children of Israel slay with the sword, among them that were slaine by them.
\v 23 And the border of the children of Reuben, was Iordan and the border therof: This was the inheritance of the children of Reuben after their families, the cities, and villages \add thereof\add*.
\v 24 And Moses gaue \add inheritance\add* vnto the tribe of Gad, \add euen\add* vnto the children of Gad, according to their families:
\v 25 And their coast was Iazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and halfe the land of the children of Ammon, vnto Aroer that \add is\add* before Rabbah:
\v 26 And from Heshbon vnto Ramath-Mizpeh, and Betonim: and from Mahanaim vnto the border of Debir.
\v 27 And in the valley, Beth-aram, and Beth-nimrah, and Succoth, and Zaphon the rest of the kingdome of Sihon king of Heshbon, Iordan, and \add his\add* border, \add euen\add* vnto the edge of the sea of Cinneroth, on the other side Iordan Eastward.
\v 28 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the children of Gad after their families: the cities and their villages.
\v 29 ¶ And Moses gaue \add inheritance\add* vnto the halfe tribe of Manasseh: and \add this\add* was \add the possession\add* of the halfe tribe of Manasseh, by their families.
\v 30 And their coast was frō Mahanaim all Bashan, all the kingdome of Og king of Bashan, and all the townes of Iair, which are in Bashan, threescore cities:
\v 31 \f + \fr 13:31 \ft Num. 32. 30.\f*And halfe Gilead, and Ashtaroth, and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan, were perteining vnto the children of Machir the sonne of Manasseh, \add euen\add* to the one halfe of the children of Machir by their families.
\v 32 These are the countreyes which Moses did distribute for inheritance in the plaines of Moab, on the other side Iordan by Iericho Eastward.
\v 33 \f + \fr 13:33 \ft Chap.18. 7.\f*\f + \fr 13:33 \ft Num. 18. 20.\f*But vnto the tribe of Leui Moses gaue not \add any\add* inheritance: the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel \add was\add* their inheritance, as he said vnto them.
\c 14
\v 0 1 The nine tribes and a halfe are to haue their inheritance by lot. 6 Caleb by priuiledge obtaineth Hebron.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 14:1 \ft Num. 34. 17.\f*And these are the countreys which the children of Israel inherited in the lande of Canaan, which Eleazar the Priest, & Ioshua the sonne of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel distributed for inheritance to them:
\v 2 \f + \fr 14:2 \ft Num. 26 55. & 33. 54.\f*By lot \add was\add* their inheritance, as the \nd LORD\nd* commanded by the hande of Moses, \add for\add* the nine tribes, and for the halfe tribe.
\v 3 For Moses had giuen the inheritance of two tribes and an halfe tribe, on the other side Iordan: but vnto the Leuites hee gaue none inheritance among them.
\v 4 For the children of Ioseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim: therefore they gaue no part vnto the Leuites in the land, saue cities to dwell \add in\add*, with their suburbs for their cattell, and for their substance.
\v 5 \f + \fr 14:5 \ft Num. 35 2. chap. 21.2.\f*As the \nd LORD\nd* commaunded Moses, so the children of Israel did, and they diuided the land.
\v 6 ¶ Then the children of Iudah came vnto Ioshua in Gilgal: and Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh the Kenezite, said vnto him, Thou knowest the thing that the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto Moses the man of God concerning me and thee, in Kadesh Barnea.
\v 7 Fourtie yeeres olde \add was\add* I when Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* sent me from Kadesh Barnea, to espie out the land, and I brought him worde againe, as \add it was\add* in mine heart.
\v 8 \f + \fr 14:8 \ft Num. 14. 24.\f*Neuerthelesse, my brethren that went vp with me, made the heart of the people melt: but I wholly followed the \nd LORD\nd* my God.
\v 9 And Moses sware on that day, saying, Surely the land whereon thy feet haue troden, shall be thine inheritance, and thy childrens for euer, because thou hast wholly followed the \nd LORD\nd* my God.
\v 10 \f + \fr 14:10 \ft Hebr. walked.\f*And now beholde, the \nd LORD\nd* hath kept me aliue, as he said, these forty and fiue yeres, euen since the \nd LORD\nd* spake this word vnto Moses, while \add the children of\add* Israel wandered in the wildernesse: and now loe, I \add am\add* this day fourescore and fiue yeeres old.
\v 11 \f + \fr 14:11 \ft Ecclus. 46.9.\f*As yet I \add am as\add* strong this day, as \add I was\add* in the day that Moses sent mee: as my strength \add was\add* then, euen so \add is\add* my strength now, for warre, both to goe out and to come in.
\v 12 Now therefore giue mee this mountaine, whereof the \nd LORD\nd* spake in that day, (for thou heardest in that day how the Anakims \add were\add* there, and \add that\add* the cities \add were\add* great \add and\add* fenced) if so be the \nd LORD\nd* \add will be\add* with me, then I shall bee able to driue them out, as the \nd LORD\nd* said.
\v 13 And Ioshua blessed him, and gaue vnto Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh, Hebron for an inheritance.
\v 14 \f + \fr 14:14 \ft Chap.21.12. 1. macc, 2.56.\f*Hebron therefore became the inheritance of Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh the Kenezite vnto this day: because that hee wholly followed the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel.
\v 15 \f + \fr 14:15 \ft Chap.15. 13.\f*And the name of Hebron before, \add was\add* Kiriath-Arba, \add which Arba was\add* a great man among the Anakims: and the land had rest from warre.
\c 15
\v 0 1 The borders of the lot of Iudah. 13 Calebs portion and conquest. 16 Othniel for his valour, hath Achsah Calebs daughter to wife. 18 Shee obtaineth a blessing of her father. 21 The Cities of Iudah. 63 The Iebusites not conquered.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 15:1 \ft Num. 34. 3.\f*\f + \fr 15:1 \ft Num. 33. 36.\f*\add This\add* then was the lot of the tribe of the children of Iudah by their families, \add euen\add* to the border of Edom; the wildernesse of Zin Southward, \add was\add* the vttermost part of the South coast:
