\v 7 \f + \fr 15:7 \ft 1.King.1. 9.\f*And the border went vp toward Debir from the valley of Achor, and so Northward, looking toward Gilgal, that \add is\add* before the going vp to Adummim, which \add is\add* on the Southside of the riuer: and the border passed towards the waters of Enshemesh, and the goings out thereof were at En-Rogel.
\v 8 And the border went vp by the valley of the sonne of Hinnom, vnto the South side of the Iebusite, the same \add is\add* Ierusalem: and the border went vp to the top of the mountaine, that \add lieth\add* before the valley of Hinnom, Westward, which \add is\add* at the end of the valley of the giants, Northward.
\v 9 And the border was drawen from the top of the hill vnto the fountaine of the water of Nephtoah, and went out to the cities of mount Ephron, and the border was drawen to Baalah, which \add is\add* Kiriath-iearim.
\v 10 And the border compassed from Baalah Westward vnto mount Seir, and passed along vnto the side of mount Iearim, (which \add is\add* Chesalon) on the North side, and went downe to Bethshemesh, and passed on to Timnah.
\v 11 And the border went out vnto the side of Ekron Northward: and the border was drawen to Shicron, and passed along to mount Baalah, and went out vnto Iabneel; and the goings out of the border were at the sea.
\v 12 And the West border \add was\add* to the great sea, and the coast therof: this \add is\add* the coast of the children of Iudah round about, according to their families.
\v 13 ¶ \f + \fr 15:13 \ft Chap. 14. 15.\f*\f + \fr 15:13 \ft Or, Kiriath-arba.\f*And vnto Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh, he gaue a part among the children of Iudah, according to the cōmandement of the \nd LORD\nd* to Ioshua, euen the citie of Arba the father of Anak, which citie is Hebron.
\v 14 \f + \fr 15:14 \ft Iudg.1.10\f*And Caleb droue thence the three sonnes of Anak, Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak.
\v 15 And he went vp thence to the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before \add was\add* Kiriath-Sepher.
\v 16 ¶ And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kiriath-Sepher, and taketh it, to him will I giue Achsah my daughter to wife.
\v 17 And Othniel the sonne of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, tooke it: and hee gaue him Achsah his daughter to wife.
\v 18 And it came to passe as shee came \add vnto him\add*, that she moued him to aske of \add her\add* father a field, and she lighted off her asse; and Caleb said vnto her, What wouldest thou?
\v 19 Who answered, Giue mee a blessing; for thou hast giuen mee a Southland, giue me also springs of water; and he gaue her the vpper springs, and the nether springs.
\v 20 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Iudah according to their families.
\v 21 And the vttermost cities of the tribe of the children of Iudah toward the coast of Edom Southward, were Kabzeel, and Eder, and Iagur,
\v 22 And Kinah, and Dimonah, and Adadah,
\v 23 And Kedesh, and Hazor, and Ithnan,
\v 24 Ziph, and Telem, and Bealoth,
\v 25 And Hazor, Hadattah, and Kerioth: \add and\add* Hezron, which \add is\add* Hazor,
\v 26 Amam, and Shema, and Moladah,
\v 27 And Hazar-Gaddah, and Heshmon, and Beth-palet,
\v 28 And Hazarshual, and Beersheba, and Biziothiah,
\v 29 Baalah, and Iim, and Azem,
\v 30 And Eltolad, and Chesil, and Hormah,
\v 31 And Ziklag, and Madmannah, and Sansannah,
\v 32 And Lebaoth, and Shilhim, and Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities \add are\add* twentie and nine, with their villages.
\v 33 \add And\add* in the valley, Esthaol, and Zoreah, and Ashnah,
\v 34 And Zanoah, and Engannim, Tappuah, and Enam,
\v 35 Iarmuth, and Adullam, Socoh, and Azekah,
\v 36 \f + \fr 15:36 \ft Or, or.\f*And Sharaim, and Adithaim, and Gederah, and Gederothaim: fourteene cities with their villages.
\v 37 Zenam, and Hadashah, & Migdalgad,
\v 38 And Dileam, and Mizpeh, and Ioktheel,
\v 39 Lachish, and Bozkath, & Eglon,
\v 40 And Cabbon, and Lahmam, and Kithlish,
\v 41 And Gederoth, Beth-dagon, and Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteene cities with their villages.
\v 42 Lebnah, and Ether, and Ashan,
\v 43 And Iiphta, and Ashnah, and Nezib,
\v 44 And Keilah, and Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages.
\v 45 Ekron with her townes, and her villages.
\v 46 \f + \fr 15:46 \ft Hebr. by the place of.\f*From Ekron euen vnto the sea, all that \add lay\add* neere Ashdod, with their villages.
\v 47 Ashdod with her townes and her villages, Gaza with her townes and her villages, vnto the riuer of Egypt, and the great sea and the border \add thereof\add*.
\v 48 ¶ And in the mountaines, Shamir, and Iattir, and Socoh,
\v 49 And Dannah, & Kiriath-Sannath, which \add is\add* Debir,
\v 50 And Anab, and Ashtemoh, and Anim,
\v 51 And Goshen, and Holon, and Giloh: eleuen cities with their villages.
\v 52 Arab, and Dumah, and Eshean,
\v 53 \f + \fr 15:53 \ft Or, Ianus.\f*And Ianum, and Beth-tappuah, and Aphekah,
\v 54 \f + \fr 15:54 \ft Chap.14. 15.\f*And Humtah, and Kiriatharba (which \add is\add* Hebron) and Zior, nine cities with their villages.
\v 55 Maon, Carmel, and Ziph, and Iuttah,
\v 56 Ind Iezreel, and Iokdeam, and Zanoah,
\v 57 Cain, Gibbeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages.
\v 58 Halhul, Beth-zur, and Gedor,
\v 59 And Maarah, and Bethanoth, & Eltekon: six cities with their villages.
\v 60 Kiriath-baal, which \add is\add* Kiriathiearim, and Rabbah: two cities with their villages.
\v 61 ¶ In the wildernesse, Beth-arabah, Middin, and Secacah,
\v 62 And Nibshan, and the city of Salt, and Engedi: sixe cities with their villages.
