\c 16
\v 0 1 The generall borders of the sonnes of Ioseph. 5 The border of the inheritance of Ephraim. 10 The Canaanites not conquered.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 16:1 \ft Hebr. went foorth.\f*And the lot of the children of Ioseph fell from Iordan by Iericho, vnto the water of Iericho on the East, to the wildernesse that goeth vp from Iericho throughout mount Bethel;
\v 2 \f + \fr 16:2 \ft Iudg.1. 26.\f*And goeth out from Bethel to Luz, and passeth along vnto the borders of Archi, to Ataroth,
\v 3 And goeth downe Westward, to the coast of Iaphleti, vnto the coast of Bethoron the nether, and to Gezer: and the goings out thereof are at the Sea.
\v 4 So the children of Ioseph, Manasseh, and Ephraim, tooke their inheritance.
\v 5 ¶ And the border of the children of Ephraim according to their families, was \add thus\add*: euen the border of their inheritance on the East side was Ataroth-Addar, vnto Bethoron the vpper.
\v 6 And the border went out toward the Sea, to Michmethah on the Northside, and the border went about Eastward vnto Taanath Shiloh, and passed by it on the East to Ianohah:
\v 7 And it went downe from Ianohah to Ataroth and to Naarath, and came to Iericho, and went out at Iordane.
\v 8 The border went out from Tappuah Westward vnto the riuer Kanah: and the goings out thereof were at the Sea. This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Ephraim by their families.
\v 9 And the separate cities for the children of Ephraim \add were\add* among the inheritance of the children of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages.
\v 10 And they draue not out the Canaanites that dwelt in Gezer: but the Canaanites dwell among the Ephramites vnto this day, and serue vnder tribute.
\c 17
\v 0 1 The lot of Manasseh. 8 His coast. 12 The Canaanites not driuen out. 14 The children of Ioseph obtaine another lot.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 17:1 \ft Gene.41 51. and 46 20. and 50. 23. num. 32.39.\f*There was also a lot for the tribe of Manasseh; ( for hee \add was\add* the first borne of Ioseph) \add to wit\add*, for Machir the first borne of Manasseh the father of Gilead: because he was a man of warre, therefore hee had Gilead and Bashan.
\v 2 \f + \fr 17:2 \ft Num.26. 29.\f*There was also \add a lot\add* for the rest of the children of Manasseh by their families; for the children of Abiezer, and for the children of Helek, and for the children of Asriel, and for the children of Shechem, and for the children of Hepher, and for the children of Shemida: these \add were\add* the male children of Manasseh, the sonne of Ioseph by their families.
\v 3 ¶ \f + \fr 17:3 \ft Num.26. 33. and 27 1. and 36.2.\f*But Zelophehad the sonne of Hepher, the sonne of Gilead, the sonne of Machir, the sonne of Manasseh, had no sonnes but daughters: And these \add are\add* the names of his daughters, Mahlah, and Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
\v 4 And they came neere before Eleazar the Priest, and before Ioshua the sonne of Nun, and before the Princes, saying, The \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses to giue vs an inheritance among our brethren: therefore according to the commaundement of the \nd LORD\nd*, hee gaue them an inheritance among the brethren of their father.
\v 5 And there fel ten portions to Manasseh, beside the land of Gilead and Bashan, which \add were\add* on the other side Iordan;
\v 6 Because the daughters of Manasseh had an inheritance among his sonnes: and the rest of Manassehs sonnes had the land of Gilead.
\v 7 ¶ And the coast of Manasseh was from Asher to Michmethah, that \add lieth\add* before Shechem, and the border went along on the right hand, vnto the inhabitants of Entappuah.
\v 8 \add Now\add* Manasseh had the land of Tappuah: but Tappuah on the border of Manasseh \add belonged\add* to the children of Ephraim.
\v 9 \f + \fr 17:9 \ft Or, brooke of reeds.\f*And the coast descended vnto the riuer Kanah, Southward of the riuer: these cities of Ephraim \add are\add* among the cities of Manasseh: the coast of Manasseh also \add was\add* on the North side of the riuer, and the outgoings of it were at the Sea.
\v 10 Southward \add it was\add* Ephraims, and Northward \add it was\add* Manassehs, and the sea is his border, and they met together in Asher on the North, and in Issachar on the East.
\v 11 And Manasseh had in Issachar and in Asher, Bethshean & her townes, and Ibleam and her townes, and the inhabitants of Dor and her townes, and the inhabitants of Endor and her townes, and the inhabitants of Taanach and her townes, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and her townes, \add euen\add* three countreyes.
\v 12 Yet the children of Manasseh could not driue out \add the inhabitants of\add* those cities, but the Canaanites would dwell in that land.
\v 13 Yet it came to passe when the children of Israel were waxen strong, that they put the Canaanites to tribute: but did not vtterly driue them out.
\v 14 And the children of Ioseph spake vnto Ioshua, saying, Why hast thou giuen me \add but\add* one lot and one portion to inherit, seeing I \add am\add* a great people, forasmuch as the \nd LORD\nd* hath blessed me hitherto?
\v 15 \f + \fr 17:15 \ft Or Rephaims.\f*And Ioshua answered them, If thou \add be\add* a great people, \add then\add* get thee vp to the wood countrey, and cut downe for thy selfe there in the land of the Perizzites, and of the giants, if mount Ephraim be too narrow for thee.
\v 16 And the children of Ioseph saide, The hill is not enough for vs: and all the Canaanites that dwell in the lande of the valley, haue charets of yron, \add both they\add* who \add are\add* of Bethshean and her townes, and \add they\add* who \add are\add* of the valley of Iezreel.
\v 17 And Ioshua spake vnto the house of Ioseph, \add euen\add* to Ephraim, and to Manasseh, saying, Thou \add art\add* a great people, and hast great power: Thou shalt not haue one lot onely.
\v 18 But the mountaine shalbe thine, for it \add is\add* a wood, \add and\add* thou shalt cut it downe: and the outgoings of it shalbe thine: for thou shalt driue out the Canaanites, though they haue yron charets, and though they \add be\add* strong.
\c 18
\v 0 1 The Tabernacle is set vp at Shiloh. 2 The remainder of the land is described, and diuided into seuen parts. 10 Ioshua diuideth it by lot. 11 The lot and border of Beniamin. 21 Their cities.
\v 1 ¶ And the whole Congregation of the children of Israel assembled together at Shiloh, & set vp the Tabernacle of the Congregation there, and the land was subdued before them.
\v 2 And there remained among the children of Israel seuen tribes, which had not yet receiued their inheritance.
\v 3 And Ioshua said vnto the children of Israel, how long \add are\add* you slacke to goe to possesse the lande which the \nd LORD\nd* God of your fathers hath giuen you?
\v 4 Giue out from among you three men, for \add each\add* tribe: and I will send them, and they shall rise, & goe through the land, and describe it according to the inheritance of them, and they shal come againe to me.
\v 5 And they shall diuide it into seuen parts: Iudah shall abide in their coast on the South, and the house of Ioseph shall abide in their coasts on the North.
\v 6 Ye shall therfore describe the land \add into\add* seuen parts, and bring \add the description\add* hither to me: that I may cast lots for you here before the \nd LORD\nd* our God.
\v 7 But the Leuites haue no part among you, for the Priesthood of the \nd LORD\nd* \add is\add* their inheritance: and Gad and Reuben, and halfe the tribe of Manasseh, haue receiued their inheritance beyond Iordan on the East, which Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* gaue them.
\v 8 ¶ And the men arose, and went away: and Ioshua charged them that went to describe the land, saying, Goe, and walke through the land, & describe it, and come againe to me, that I may here cast lots for you, before the \nd LORD\nd* in Shiloh.
\v 9 And the men went, and passed thorow the land, and described it by cities, into seuen parts in a booke, and came againe to Ioshua to the hoste at Shiloh.
\v 10 ¶ And Ioshua cast lots for them in Shiloh, before the \nd LORD\nd*: and there Ioshua diuided the land vnto the children of Israel according to their diuisions.
\v 11 ¶ And the lot of the tribe of the children of Beniamin came vp according to their families: and the coast of their lot came foorth betweene the children of Iudah, and the children of Ioseph.
\v 12 And their border on the Northside was from Iordan, and the border went vp to the side of Iericho, on the North side, and went vp through the mountaines Westward, and the goings out thereof were at the wildernesse of Beth-auen.
\v 13 And the border went ouer from thence toward Luz, to the side of Luz, (which \add is\add* Bethel) Southward, and the border descended to Ataroth-Adar, neere the hill that \add lieth\add* on the South side of the nether Beth-horon.
\v 14 And the border was drawen \add thence\add*, and compassed the corner of the Sea Southward, from the hill that \add lieth\add* before Beth-horon Southward: and the goings out thereof were at Kiriath-baal (which \add is\add* Kiriath-iearim) a city of the children of Iudah: This \add was\add* the West quarter.
\v 15 And the South quarter \add was\add* from the end of Kiriath-iearim, & the border went out on the West, and went out to the well of waters of Nephtoah.
\v 16 And the border came downe to the end of the mountaine, that \add lieth\add* before the valley of the sonne of Hinnom, \add and\add* which \add is\add* in the valley of the Giants on the North, and descended to the valley of Hinnom to the side of Iebusi on the South, and descended to En-Rogel,
\v 17 \f + \fr 18:17 \ft Chap.15. 6.\f*And was drawen frō the North, and went foorth to Enshemesh, and went foorth toward Geliloth, which is ouer against the going vp of Adummim, and descended to the stone of Bohan the sonne of Reuben,
\v 18 \f + \fr 18:18 \ft Or, the plaine.\f*And passed along toward the side ouer against Arabah Northward, and went downe vnto Arabah.
\v 19 \f + \fr 18:19 \ft Hebr. tongue.\f*And the border passed along to the side of Beth-hoglah Northward: and the outgoings of the border were at the North bay of the salt Sea at the South end of Iordane: This \add was\add* the South coast.
\v 20 And Iordane was the border of it on the East side: this \add was\add* the inheritance of the children of Beniamin, by the coasts thereof round about, according to their families.
\v 21 Now the cities of the tribe of the children of Beniamin according to their families, were Iericho, and Bethhoglah, and the valley of Keziz,
\v 22 And Betharabah, and Zemaraim, and Bethel,
\v 23 And Auim, and Parah, and Ophrah,
\v 24 And Chephar-Haammonai, and Ophni, and Gaba, twelue cities with their villages.
\v 25 Gibeon, and Ramah, and Beeroth,
\v 26 And Mizpeh, and Chephirah, and Mozah,
\v 27 And Rekem, and Irpeel, and Taralah,
\v 28 And Zela, Eleph, and Iebusi, (which \add is\add* Ierusalem) Gibeath, \add and\add* Kiriath, foureteene cities with their villages. This \add is\add* the inheritance of the children of Beniamin according to their families.
\c 19
\v 0 1 The lot of Simeon, 10 Of Zebulun, 17 Of Issachar, 24 Of Asher, 32 Of Naphtali, 40 Of Dan. 46 The children of Israel giue an inheritance to Ioshua.
\v 1 ¶ And the second lot came foorth to Simeon, \add euen\add* for the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families: and their inheritance was within the inheritance of the children of Iudah.
\v 2 And they had in their inheritance Beer-sheba, or Sheba, and Moladah,
\v 3 And Hazarshual, and Balah, and Azem,
\v 4 And Eltolad, and Bethul, and Hormah,
\v 5 And Ziklag, and Beth-marcaboth, and Hazar-susah,
\v 6 And Beth-lebaoth, and Sharuhen: thirteene cities and their villages.
\v 7 Ain, Remmon, and Ether, and Ashan: foure cities and their villages,
\v 8 And all the villages that \add were\add* round about these cities, to Baalath-Beer, Ramath of the South: This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families.
\v 9 Out of the portion of the children of Iudah \add was\add* the inheritance of the children of Simeon: for the part of the children of Iudah was too much for them: therefore the children of Simeon had their inheritance within the inheritance of them.
\v 10 ¶ And the third lot came vp for the children of Zebulun, according to their families: and the border of their inheritance was vnto Sarid.
\v 11 And their border went vp toward the Sea, and Maralah, and reached to Dabbasheth, and reached to the riuer that \add is\add* before Iokneam,
\v 12 And turned from Sarid Eastward, toward the Sunne rising, vnto the border of Chisloth Tabor, and then goeth out to Daberath, and goeth vp to Iaphia,
\v 13 \f + \fr 19:13 \ft Or, which is drawen.\f*And from thence passeth on along on the East to Gittah-Hepher, to Ittah-Kazin, and goeth out to Remmon Methoar to Neah.
\v 14 And the border compasseth it on the North side to Hannathon: and the outgoings thereof are in the valley of Iiphthah-el.
\v 15 And Kattath, and Nahallal, and Shimron, and Idalah, and Bethlehem: twelue cities with their villages.
\v 16 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the children of Zebulun according to their families, these cities with their villages.
\v 17 ¶ \add And\add* the fourth lot came out to Issachar for the children of Issachar according to their families.
\v 18 And their border was toward Izreel, and Chesulloth, and Shunem,
\v 19 And Hapharaim, and Shion, and Anaharath,
\v 20 And Rabbith, and Kishion, and Abez,
\v 21 And Remeth, and Engannim, and Enhaddah, and Bethpazzez.
\v 22 And the coast reacheth to Tabor, and Shahazimath, and Bethshemesh, and the outgoings of their border were at Iordan, sixteene cities with their villages.
\v 23 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Issachar according to their families, the cities, and their villages.
\v 24 ¶ And the fift lot came out for the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families.
\v 25 And their border was Helkath, and Hali, and Beten, and Achshaph,
\v 26 And Alammelech, and Amad, and Misheal, and reacheth to Carmel westward, and to Shihor-Libnath,
\v 27 And turneth toward the Sunne rising to Beth-dagon, and reacheth to Zebulun, and to the valley of of Iiphthahel toward the Northside of Bethemek, and Neiel, and goeth out to Cabul on the left hand,
\v 28 And Hebron, and Rehob, and Hammon, and Kanah, \add euen\add* vnto great Zidon:
\v 29 \f + \fr 19:29 \ft Heb. Tzor.\f*And \add then\add* the coast turneth to Ramah, and to the strong citie Tyre, and the coast turneth to Hosah: and the outgoings thereof are at the Sea from the coast to Achzib.
\v 30 Ummah also, and Aphek, and Rehob: twentie and two cities with their villages.
\v 31 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families, these cities with their villages.
\v 32 ¶ The sixt lot came out to the children of Naphtali: \add euen\add* for the children of Naphtali according to their families.
\v 33 And their coast was from Heleph, from Allon to Zaanannim, and Adami, Nekeb, and Iabneel vnto Lakum: and the outgoings thereof were at Iordan.
\v 34 And \add then\add* the coast turneth westward to Aznoth-Tabor, and goeth out from thence to Hukkok, and reacheth to Zebulun on the Southside, and reacheth to Asher on the Westside, and to Iudah vpon Iordan toward the Sun rising.
\v 35 And the fenced cities \add are\add* Ziddim, Zer, and Hammath, Rakkath, and Cinnereth,
\v 36 And Adamah, and Ramah, and Hazor,
\v 37 And Kedesh, and Edrei, and Enhazor,
\v 38 And Iron, and Migdal-el, Horem, and Bethanah, and Bethshemesh, nineteene cities with their villages.
\v 39 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali according to their families, the cities and their villages.
\v 40 ¶ \add And\add* the seuenth lot came out for the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families:
\v 41 And the coast of their inheritance was Zorah, and Eshtaol, and Irshemesh,
\v 42 And Shaalabbin, and Aiialon, and Iethlah,
\v 43 And Elon, and Thimnathah, and Ekron,
\v 44 And Eltekeh, and Gibbethon, and Baalah,
\v 45 And Iehud, and Bene-berak, and Gath-rimmon,
\v 46 \f + \fr 19:46 \ft Or, ouer against.\f*\f + \fr 19:46 \ft Or, Ioppa, Acts.9.36.\f*And Meiarkon, and Rakkon, with the border before Iapho.
\v 47 \f + \fr 19:47 \ft Iudg.18. 19.\f*And the coast of the children of Dan went out \add too little\add* for them: therefore the children of Dan went vp to fight against Leshem, and tooke it, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and possessed it, and dwelt therein, and called Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their father.
\v 48 This \add is\add* the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families, these cities with their villages.
\v 49 ¶ When they had made an end of diuiding the land for inheritance by their coasts, the children of Israel gaue an inheritance to Ioshua the sonne of Nun among them:
\v 50 \f + \fr 19:50 \ft Chap.24. 30.\f*According to the word of the \nd LORD\nd*, they gaue him the citie which he asked, \add euen\add* Timnath-Serah in mount Ephraim: and he built the citie, and dwelt therein.
\v 51 \f + \fr 19:51 \ft Num.34. 17.\f*These \add are\add* the inheritances which Eleazar the Priest, and Ioshua the sonne of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel, diuided for an inheritance by lot, in Shiloh before the \nd LORD\nd*, at the doore of the Tabernacle of the Congregation: so they made an end of diuiding the countrey.
\c 20
\v 0 1 God commandeth, 7 and the children of Israel appoint the sixe cities of Refuge.
\v 1 ¶ The \nd LORD\nd* also spake vnto Ioshua, saying,
\v 2 \f + \fr 20:2 \ft Exod.21. 13. num. 35.6,11. 14. deut.19.2.\f*Speake to the children of Israel, saying, Appoint out for you cities of refuge, whereof I spake vnto you by the hand of Moses:
\v 3 That the slayer that killeth \add any\add* person vnawares \add and\add* vnwittingly, may flee thither: and they shall be your refuge from the auenger of blood.
\v 4 And when he that doeth flee vnto one of those cities, shall stand at the entring of the gate of the city, and shall declare his cause in the eares of the Elders of that citie; they shall take him into the citie vnto them, and giue him a place, that he may dwell among them.
\v 5 And if the auenger of blood pursue after him, then they shal not deliuer the slayer vp into his hand: because hee smote his neighbour vnwittingly, and hated him not beforetime.
\v 6 \f + \fr 20:6 \ft Num.35. 25.\f*And hee shall dwell in that citie, vntill he stand before the Congregation for iudgement, \add and\add* vntill the death of the high Priest that shall bee in those dayes: then shall the slayer returne, and come vnto his owne city, and vnto his owne house, vnto the citie from whence he fled.
\v 7 ¶ \f + \fr 20:7 \ft Hebr. sanctified.\f*And they appointed Kedesh in Galilee, in mount Naphtali, and Shechem in mount Ephraim, and Kiriath-arba (which \add is\add* Hebron) in the mountaine of Iudah.
\v 8 \f + \fr 20:8 \ft Deut.4 43. 1.chro. 6.78.\f*And on the other side Iordan by Iericho Eastward, they assigned Bezer in the wildernesse vpon the plaine, out of the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead out of the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan out of the tribe of Manasseh.
\v 9 These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel, and for the stranger that soiourneth among them, that whosoeuer killeth \add any\add* person at vnawares might flee thither, & not die by the hand of the auenger of blood, vntill he stood before the Congregation.
\c 21
\v 0 1 Eight and fortie cities giuen by lot, out of the other tribes, vnto the Leuites. 43 God gaue the land, and rest vnto the Israelites, according to his promise.
\v 1 ¶ Then came neere the heads of the fathers of the Leuites vnto Eleazar the Priest, and vnto Ioshua the sonne of Nun, and vnto the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel.
\v 2 \f + \fr 21:2 \ft Num.35. 2.\f*And they spake vnto them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, The \nd LORD\nd* commaunded by the hand of Moses, to giue vs Cities to dwell in, with the suburbs thereof for our cattell.
\v 3 And the children of Israel gaue vnto the Leuites out of their inheritance at the commandement of the \nd LORD\nd*, these cities and their suburbs.
\v 4 And the lot came out for the families of the Kohathites: and the children of Aaron the Priest, \add which were\add* of the Leuites, had by lot out of the tribe of Iudah, and out of the tribe of Simeon, and out of the tribe of Beniamin, thirteene cities.
\v 5 And the rest of the children of Kohath \add had\add* by lot, out of the families of the tribe of Ephraim, and out of the tribe of Dan, and out of the halfe tribe of Manasseh, ten cities.
\v 6 And the children of Gershon \add had\add* by lot out of the families of the tribe of Issachar, and out of the tribe of Asher, and out of the tribe of Naphtali, and out of the halfe tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteene cities.
\v 7 The children of Merari by their families, \add had\add* out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of Gad, and out of the tribe of Zebulun, twelue cities.
\v 8 And the children of Israel gaue by lot vnto the Leuites these cities with their suburbs, as the \nd LORD\nd* commanded by the hand of Moses.
\v 9 ¶ \f + \fr 21:9 \ft Hebr. called.\f*And they gaue out of the tribe of the children of Iudah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, these cities which are \add here\add* mentioned by name,
\v 10 Which the children of Aaron \add being\add* of the families of the Kohathites, \add who were\add* of the children of Leui, had: (for theirs was the first lot.)
\v 11 \f + \fr 21:11 \ft Or, Kiriath-arbah.\f*And they gaue them the citie of Arbah the father of Anak (which citie is Hebron) in the hill countrey of Iudah, with y\sup e\sup* suburbs thereof round about it.
\v 12 \f + \fr 21:12 \ft Chap.14 14. 1.chro. 6.56.\f*But the fields of the citie, and the villages thereof, gaue they to Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh, for his possession.
\v 13 ¶ Thus they gaue to the children of Aaron the Priest Hebron with her suburbs \add to bee\add* a citie of refuge for the slayer, and Libnah with her suburbs,
\v 14 And Iattir with her suburbs, and Eshtemoa with her suburbs:
\v 15 And Holon with her suburbs, and Debir with her suburbs:
\v 16 And Ain with her suburbs, and Iuttah with her suburbs, \add and\add* Bethshemesh with her suburbs, nine cities out of those two tribes.
\v 17 And out of the tribe of Beniamin, Gibeon with her suburbs, Geba with her suburbs,
\v 18 Anathoth with her suburbs, and Almon with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 19 All the cities of the children of Aaron the Priests, \add were\add* thirteene cities with their suburbs.
\v 20 ¶ And the families of the children of Kohath the Leuites, which remained of the children of Kohath, euen they had the cities of their lot out of the tribe of Ephraim.
\v 21 For they gaue them Shechem with her suburbs in mount Ephraim, \add to be\add* a citie of refuge for the slayer: and Gezer with her suburbs,
\v 22 And Kibzaim with her suburbs, and Beth-horon with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 23 And out of the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh with her suburbs, Gibethon with her suburbs,
\v 24 Aijalon with her suburbs, Gathrimmon, with her suburbs: foure cities.
\v 25 And out of the halfe tribe of Manasseh, Tanach with her suburbs, and Gathrimmon with her suburbs, two cities.
\v 26 All the cities \add were\add* ten with their suburbs, for the families of the children of Kohath that remained.
\v 27 ¶ And vnto the children of Gershon of the families of the Leuites, out of the \add other\add* halfe tribe of Manasseh, \add they gaue\add* Golan in Bashan, with her suburbs, \add to be\add* a citie of refuge for the slayer: and Beeshterah with her suburbs, two cities.
\v 28 And out of the tribe of Issachar, Kishon with her suburbs, Dabareh with her suburbs,
\v 29 Iarmuth with her suburbs, Engannim with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 30 And out of the tribe of Asher Mishal with her suburbs, Abdon with her suburbs,
\v 31 Helkah with her suburbs, and Rehob with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 32 And out of the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with her suburbs, \add to be\add* a citie of refuge for the slayer, and Hammoth-dor with her suburbs, and Kartan with her suburbs, three cities.
\v 33 All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families \add were\add* thirteen cities with their suburbs.
\v 34 ¶ And vnto the families of the children of Merari the rest of the Leuites, out of the tribe of Zebulun, Iokneam, with her suburbs, and Kartah with her suburbs,
\v 35 Dimnah with her suburbs, Nahalal with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 36 And out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with her suburbs, and Iahazah with her suburbs,
\v 37 Kedemoth with her suburbs, and Mephaath with her suburbs, foure cities.
\v 38 And out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with her suburbs, \add to be\add* a city of refuge for the slayer; and Mahanaim with her suburbs,
\v 39 Heshbon with her suburbs, Iazer with her suburbs, foure cities in all.
\v 40 So all the cities for the children of Merari by their families, which were remayning of the families of the Leuites, were \add by\add* their lot, twelue cities.
\v 41 All the cities of the Leuites within the possession of the children of Israel, \add were\add* fourty and eight cities, with their suburbs.
\v 42 These cities were euery one with their suburbs round about them: thus \add were\add* all these cities.
\v 43 ¶ And the \nd LORD\nd* gaue vnto Israel all the land which hee sware to giue vnto their fathers: and they possessed it, and dwelt therein.
\v 44 And the \nd LORD\nd* gaue them rest round about, according to all that he sware vnto their fathers, and there stood not a man of all their enemies before them: the \nd LORD\nd* deliuered all their enemies into their hand.
\v 45 \f + \fr 21:45 \ft Chap.23.14,15.\f*There failed not ought of any good thing which the \nd LORD\nd* had spoken vnto the house of Israel: all came to passe.
\c 22
\v 0 1 The two Tribes and halfe with a blessing are sent home. 9 They build the Altar of Testimony, in their iourney. 11 The Israelites are offended thereat. 21 They giue them good satisfaction.
\v 1 ¶ Then Ioshua called the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh,
\v 2 And said vnto them, Yee haue kept all that Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* commanded you, and haue obeyed my voyce in all that I commanded you.
\v 3 Yee haue not left your brethren these many dayes vnto this day, but haue kept the charge of the commandement of the \nd LORD\nd* your God.
\v 4 \f + \fr 22:4 \ft Num.32. 33. chap.13.8.\f*And now the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath giuen rest vnto your brethren, as hee promised them: therefore now returne yee, and get yee vnto your tents, \add and\add* vnto the land of your possession, which Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* gaue you on the other side Iordane.
\v 5 \f + \fr 22:5 \ft Deut.10. 12.\f*But take diligent heed, to doe the Commandement and the Law, which Moses the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* charged you, to loue the \nd LORD\nd* your God, and to walke in all his wayes, and to keepe his Commaundements, and to cleaue vnto him, and to serue him with all your heart, and with all your soule.
\v 6 So Ioshua blessed them, and sent them away: and they went vnto their tents.
\v 7 ¶ Now to the \add one\add* halfe of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had giuen \add possession\add* in Bashan: but vnto the \add other\add* halfe therof gaue Ioshua among their brethren on this side Iordane Westward. And when Ioshua sent them away also vnto their tents, then hee blessed them,
\v 8 And he spake vnto them, saying; Returne with much riches vnto your tents, and with very much cattell, with siluer and with gold, and with brasse, and with iron, and with very much raiment: Diuide the spoile of your enemies with your brethren.
\v 9 ¶ And the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh returned, and departed from the children of Israel out of Shiloh which \add is\add* in the land of Canaan, to goe vnto the countrey of Gilead, to the land of their possession, whereof they were possessed, according to the word of the \nd LORD\nd* by the hand of Moses.
\v 10 ¶ And when they came vnto the borders of Iordan, that \add are\add* in the land of Canaan, the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh built there an altar by Iordan, a great altar to see to.
\v 11 ¶ And the children of Israel heard say, Behold, the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh, haue built an altar ouer against the land of Canaan, in the borders of Iordan, at the passage of the children of Israel.
\v 12 And when the children of Israel heard \add of it\add*, the whole Congregation of the children of Israel gathered themselues together at Shiloh, to goe vp to warre against them.
\v 13 And the children of Israel sent vnto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the halfe tribe of Manasseh into the lande of Gilead, Phinehas son of Eleazar the Priest,
\v 14 \f + \fr 22:14 \ft Heb. house of the father.\f*And with him ten princes, of ech chiefe house a prince, throughout all the tribes of Israel, and each one \add was\add* an head of the house of their fathers, among the thousands of Israel.
\v 15 ¶ And they came vnto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the halfe tribe of Manasseh vnto the land of Gilead, and they spake with them, saying,
\v 16 Thus saith the whole Congregation of the \nd LORD\nd*, What trespasse \add is\add* this that ye haue committed against the God of Israel, to turne away this day from following the \nd LORD\nd*, in that ye haue builded you an altar, that yee might rebell this day against the \nd LORD\nd*?
\v 17 \f + \fr 22:17 \ft Num. 25.\f*\add Is\add* the iniquitie of Peor too litle for vs, from which we are not cleansed vntil this day, (although there was a plague in the Congregation of the \nd LORD\nd*)
\v 18 But that ye must turne away this day from following the \nd LORD\nd*? And it will be, \add seeing\add* yee rebell to day against the \nd LORD\nd*, that to morrow he will be wroth with the whole Congregation of Israel.
\v 19 Notwithstanding, if the lande of your possession \add be\add* vncleane, \add then\add* passe yee ouer vnto the land of the possession of the \nd LORD\nd*, wherein the \nd LORD\nd*s Tabernacle dwelleth, and take possession among vs: but rebell not against the \nd LORD\nd*, nor rebell against vs, in building you an altar, beside the Altar of the \nd LORD\nd* our God.
\v 20 \f + \fr 22:20 \ft Chap. 7. 1,5.\f*Did not Achan the sonne of Zerah commit a trespasse in the accursed thing, and wrath fell on all the Congregation of Israel? and that man perished not alone in his iniquitie.
\v 21 ¶ Then the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad, and the halfe tribe of Manasseh, answered and saide vnto the heads of the thousands of Israel,
\v 22 The \nd LORD\nd* God of gods, the \nd LORD\nd* God of gods, hee knoweth, and Israel he shall know; if it bee in rebellion, or if in transgression against the \nd LORD\nd*, (saue vs not this day,)
\v 23 That wee haue built vs an altar to turne from following the \nd LORD\nd*, or if to offer thereon burnt offering, or meat offering, or if to offer peace offerings thereon, let the \nd LORD\nd* himselfe require \add it\add*;
\v 24 \f + \fr 22:24 \ft Hebr. to morrow.\f*And if we haue not \add rather\add* done it for feare of \add this\add* thing, saying, In time to come your children might speake vnto our children, saying, What haue you to doe with the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel?
\v 25 For the \nd LORD\nd* hath made Iordan a border betweene vs and you, yee children of Reuben, and children of Gad, yee haue no part in the \nd LORD\nd*: so shal your children make our children cease from fearing the \nd LORD\nd*:
\v 26 Therefore we said, Let vs now prepare to build vs an altar, not for burnt offering, nor for sacrifice,
\v 27 \f + \fr 22:27 \ft Gen. 31. 48. chap. 24 27. ver. 34.\f*But \add that\add* it may bee a witnesse betweene vs and you, and our generations after vs, that we might do the seruice of the \nd LORD\nd* before him with our burnt offrings, and with our sacrifices, and with our peace offerings, that your children may not say to our children in time to come, Ye haue no part in the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 28 Therefore said we, that it shalbe, when they should \add so\add* say to vs, or to our generations in time to come, that wee may say againe, Beholde the paterne of the altar of the \nd LORD\nd*, which our fathers made, not for burnt offrings, nor for sacrifices, but it \add is\add* a witnes betweene vs and you.
\v 29 God forbid that we should rebell against the \nd LORD\nd*, and turne this day from following the \nd LORD\nd*, to build an altar for burnt offerings, for meate offerings, or for sacrifices, besides the Altar of the \nd LORD\nd* our God that \add is\add* before his Tabernacle.
\v 30 ¶ \f + \fr 22:30 \ft Hebr. it was good in their eyes.\f*And when Phinehas the Priest and the Princes of the Congregation, and Heads of the thousands of Israel which \add were\add* with him, heard the words that the children of Reuben and the children of Gad, and the children of Manasseh spake, it pleased them.
\v 31 \f + \fr 22:31 \ft Hebr. Then.\f*And Phinehas the sonne of Eleazar the Priest said vnto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the children of Manasseh, This day we perceiue that the \nd LORD\nd* \add is\add* among vs, because ye haue not committed this trespasse against the \nd LORD\nd*: now ye haue deliuered the children of Israel out of the hand of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 32 ¶ And Phinehas the sonne of Eleazar the Priest, and the Princes, returned from the children of Reuben, and from the children of Gad, out of the land of Gilead, vnto the land of Canaan, to the children of Israel, & brought them word againe.
\v 33 And the thing pleased the children of Israel, and the children of Israel blessed God, and did not intend to goe vp against them in battel, to destroy the land wherein the children of Reuben and Gad dwelt.
\v 34 \f + \fr 22:34 \ft That is, a witnesse.\f*And the children of Reuben, and the children of Gad called the altar \add Ed\add*: for it shall bee a witnesse betweene vs, that the \nd LORD\nd* \add is\add* God.
\c 23
\v 0 1 Ioshuas exhortation before his death, 3 by former benefits, 5 by promises, 11 and by threatnings.
\v 1 ¶ \f + \fr 23:1 \ft Heb. come into dayes.\f*And it came to passe, a long time after that the \nd LORD\nd* had giuen rest vnto Israel from all their enemies round about, that Ioshua waxed old, \add and\add* stricken in age.
\v 2 And Ioshua called for all Israel, \add and\add* for their Elders, & for their Heads, \add and\add* for their Iudges, and for their Officers, and said vnto them; I am old, and stricken in age.
\v 3 \f + \fr 23:3 \ft Exod. 14. 4.\f*And yee haue seene all that the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath done vnto all these nations, because of you; for the \nd LORD\nd* your God \add is\add* hee that hath fought for you.
\v 4 \f + \fr 23:4 \ft Hebr. at the Sunne set.\f*Behold, I haue diuided vnto you by lot these nations that remaine, to bee an inheritance for your tribes, from Iordan, with all the nations that I haue cut off, euen vnto the great Sea Westward.
\v 5 And the \nd LORD\nd* your God, hee shall expell them from before you, and driue them from out of your sight, & ye shall possesse their land, as the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath promised vnto you.
\v 6 \f + \fr 23:6 \ft Deut. 5. 32.and 28. 14.\f*Be ye therefore very courageous to keepe and to doe all that is written in the booke of the Law of Moses, that yee turne not aside therefrom, \add to\add* the right hand, or \add to\add* the left,
\v 7 \f + \fr 23:7 \ft Psal. 16.4.\f*That yee come not among these nations, these that remaine amongst you, neither make mention of the name of their gods, nor cause to sweare \add by them\add*, neither serue them, nor bow your selues vnto them.
\v 8 \f + \fr 23:8 \ft Or, for if you will cleaue, &c.\f*But cleaue vnto the \nd LORD\nd* your God, as yee haue done vnto this day.
\v 9 \f + \fr 23:9 \ft Or, then the LORD will driue.\f*For the \nd LORD\nd* hath driuen out from before you, great nations, and strong: But \add as for\add* you, no man hath beene able to stand before you vnto this day.
\v 10 \f + \fr 23:10 \ft Leuit. 26. 8. deut. 32. 30.\f*One man of you shall chase a thousand: for the \nd LORD\nd* your God, he \add it is\add* that fighteth for you, as hee hath promised you.
\v 11 \f + \fr 23:11 \ft Heb. soules.\f*Take good heed therefore vnto your selues, that ye loue the \nd LORD\nd* your God.
\v 12 Else, if ye do in any wise go backe, and cleaue vnto the remnant of these nations, \add euen\add* these that remaine among you, and shall make marriages with them, and goe in vnto them, and they to you:
\v 13 \f + \fr 23:13 \ft Exod. 23. 33. numb. 33.55. deu 7.16.\f*Know for a certainety, that the \nd LORD\nd* your God will no more driue out \add any of\add* these nations from before you: but they shalbe snares and traps vnto you, and scourges in your sides, and thornes in your eyes, vntill yee perish from off this good land which the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath giuen you.
\v 14 \f + \fr 23:14 \ft Chap. 21. 45.\f*And behold, this day I \add am\add* going the way of all the earth, \add and\add* ye know in all your hearts, and in all your soules, that not one thing hath failed of all the good things which the \nd LORD\nd* your God spake concerning you; all are come to passe vnto you, and not one thing hath failed thereof.
\v 15 Therefore it shall come to passe, \add that\add* as all good things are come vpon you, which the \nd LORD\nd* your God promised you: so shall the \nd LORD\nd* bring vpon you all euill things, vntill he haue destroyed you from off this good land which the \nd LORD\nd* your God hath giuen you.
\v 16 When yee haue transgressed the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd* your God, which hee commaunded you, and haue gone and serued other gods, and bowed your selues to them: then shall the anger of the \nd LORD\nd* bee kindled against you, and yee shall perish quickly from off the good land which hee hath giuen vnto you.
\c 24
\v 0 1 Ioshua assembleth the tribes at Shechem. 2 A briefe historie of Gods benefits from Terah. 14 He reneweth a couenant betweene them and God. 26 A stone the witnesse of the couenant. 29 Ioshuas age, death and buriall. 32 Iosephs bones are buried. 33 Eleazar dieth.
\v 1 ¶ And Ioshua gathered all the Tribes of Israel to Shechem, and called for the Elders of Israel, and for their Heads, and for their Iudges, and for their Officers, and they presented themselues before God.
\v 2 \f + \fr 24:2 \ft Gen. 11. 31. iudit. 5. 6,7.\f*And Ioshua said vnto all the people, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel, Your fathers dwelt on the other side of the flood in old time, \add euen\add* Terah the father of Abraham, and the father of Nachor: and they serued other gods.
\v 3 \f + \fr 24:3 \ft Gen. 21. 2\f*And I tooke your father Abraham frō the other side of the flood, and led him throughout all the land of Canaan, and multiplied his seed, and gaue him Isaac.
\v 4 \f + \fr 24:4 \ft Gen. 25. 26.\f*\f + \fr 24:4 \ft Gen. 36.8\f*\f + \fr 24:4 \ft Gen. 46.6\f*And I gaue vnto Isaac, Iacob and Esau: & I gaue vnto Esau mount Seir, to possesse it: but Iacob and his children went downe into Egypt.
\v 5 \f + \fr 24:5 \ft Exo. 3. 10\f*I sent Moses also and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt, according to that which I did amongst them: and afterward, I brought you out.
\v 6 \f + \fr 24:6 \ft Exod. 12. 37.\f*\f + \fr 24:6 \ft Exod.14. 9.\f*And I brought your fathers out of Egypt: and you came vnto the sea, and the Egyptians pursued after your fathers with charets and horsemen vnto the red sea.
\v 7 And when they cried vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, hee put darkenesse betweene you and the Egyptians, and brought the sea vpon them, and couered them, and your eyes haue seene what I haue done in Egypt, and ye dwelt in the wildernes a long season.
\v 8 \f + \fr 24:8 \ft Num.21 33.\f*And I brought you into the land of the Amorites, which dwelt on the other side Iordan: and they fought with you, and I gaue them into your hand, that ye might possesse their land, and I destroyed them from before you.
\v 9 \f + \fr 24:9 \ft Num. 22. 5. deut. 23. 4\f*Then Balak the sonne of Zippor king of Moab, arose and warred against Israel, and sent and called Balaam the sonne of Beor to curse you:
\v 10 But I would not hearken vnto Balaam, therefore he blessed you still: so I deliuered you out of his hand.
\v 11 And ye went ouer Iordan, and came vnto Iericho: and the men of Iericho fought against you, the Amorites, and the Perizzites, & the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Girgashites, the Hiuites, and the Iebusites, and I deliuered them into your hand.
\v 12 \f + \fr 24:12 \ft Exod. 23. 28. deut.7. 20.\f*And I sent the hornet before you, which draue them out from before you, \add euen\add* the two kings of the Amorites: \add but\add* not with thy sword, nor with thy bow.
\v 13 And I haue giuen you a land for which ye did not labour, & cities which ye built not, and yee dwell in them: of the vineyards and Oliue-yards which ye planted not, doe ye eate.
\v 14 ¶ Now therefore, feare the \nd LORD\nd*, and serue him in sinceritie, and in trueth, and put away the gods which your fathers serued on the other side of the flood, and in Egypt: and serue yee the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 15 And if it seeme euill vnto you to serue the \nd LORD\nd*, choose you this day whome you will serue, whether the gods which your fathers serued that \add were\add* on the other side of the flood, or the gods of the Amorites, in whose lande ye dwell: but as for mee and my house, we will serue the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 16 And the people answered and said, God forbid that wee should forsake the \nd LORD\nd*, to serue other gods.
\v 17 For the \nd LORD\nd* our God, he \add it is\add* that brought vs vp and our fathers out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage, & which did those great signes in our sight, and preserued vs in all the way wherein we went, and among all the people through whom we passed.
\v 18 And the \nd LORD\nd* draue out from before vs all the people, euen the Amorites which dwelt in the land: \add therefore\add* will we also serue the \nd LORD\nd*, for he \add is\add* our God.
\v 19 And Ioshua said vnto the people, Ye cannot serue the \nd LORD\nd*: for hee \add is\add* an holy God: he \add is\add* a ielous God, he will not forgiue your transgressions nor your sinnes.
\v 20 \f + \fr 24:20 \ft Chap. 23. 15.\f*If yee forsake the \nd LORD\nd*, and serue strange gods, then he will turne, and doe you hurt, and consume you, after that he hath done you good.
\v 21 And the people said vnto Ioshua, Nay, but we will serue the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 22 And Ioshua said vnto the people, Yee \add are\add* witnesses against your selues, that yee haue chosen you the \nd LORD\nd*, to serue him. And they said, \add We are\add* witnesses.
\v 23 Now therefore put away, \add said he\add*, the strange gods which \add are\add* among you, and encline your heart vnto the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel.
\v 24 And the people saide vnto Ioshua; The \nd LORD\nd* our God will we serue, and his voice will we obey.
\v 25 So Ioshua made a couenant with the people that day, and set them a Statute, & an Ordinance in Shechem.
\v 26 ¶ And Ioshua wrote these words in the booke of the Law of God, and tooke a great stone, and set it vp there, vnder an oake, that \add was\add* by the Sanctuary of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 27 And Ioshua saide vnto all the people, Behold, this stone shalbe a witnesse vnto vs; for it hath heard all the words of the \nd LORD\nd* which hee spake vnto vs; it shall be there for a witnesse vnto you, lest ye deny your God.
\v 28 So Ioshua let the people depart, euery man vnto his inheritance.
\v 29 ¶ And it came to passe after these things, that Ioshua the sonne of Nun the seruant of the \nd LORD\nd* died, \add being\add* an hundred and ten yeeres old.
\v 30 \f + \fr 24:30 \ft Chap. 19. 50. iudg.2. 9.\f*And they buried him in the border of his inheritance in Timnath-Serah, which \add is\add* in mount Ephraim, on the North side of the hill of Gaash.
\v 31 \f + \fr 24:31 \ft Hebr. prolonged their dayes after Ioshua.\f*And Israel serued the \nd LORD\nd* all the dayes of Ioshua, & all the dayes of the Elders that ouerliued Ioshua, and which had knowen al the works of the \nd LORD\nd*, that he had done for Israel.
\v 32 ¶ \f + \fr 24:32 \ft Gen. 50. 25. exod. 13.19.\f*\f + \fr 24:32 \ft Gene. 33. 19.\f*\f + \fr 24:32 \ft Or, lambs.\f*And the bones of Ioseph, which the children of Israel brought vp out of Egypt, buried they in Shechem, in a parcell of ground which Iacob bought of the sonnes of Hamor the father of Shechem, for an hundred pieces of siluer; and it became the inheritance of the children of Ioseph.
\v 33 And Eleazar the sonne of Aaron died, and they buried him in a hill \add that pertained to\add* Phinehas his son, which was giuen him in mount Ephraim.
